stems that are older and/or cannot be repaired.</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\"><strong>Furnace maintenance</strong></a> for keeping your unit healthy and working all year long.</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a title=\"Furnace Installation \" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></strong> for new systems.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe start with a full diagnostic analysis of your current system and your home so we can identify the right furnace to fit the space that you have. Even though some people think bigger is better, when it comes to your heating and cooling system, having a furnace that is too large or too small for your home can waste energy and cost you money.\r\n\r\nOur experienced repair and installation technicians can help you find the system that is right for you, and get it installed quickly and easily. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air technicians have all passed background checks, are trained in the latest industry advancements and trends, and equipped with state-of-the-art tools and technology to diagnose and solve your furnace problems.\r\n<h2>How Furnaces Work</h2>\r\nYour furnace heats your home by taking cool air from throughout your home, heating it, then distributing it through a series of ducts. There are three main types of furnaces available today.\r\n<h3>Natural Gas Furnace</h3>\r\nA natural gas furnace, also called a forced-air furnace, pulls cool air from the rooms then passes it through a heat exchanger where the gas ignites a burner inside a combustion chamber. The warm air is distributed back to the rooms through the same duct system, and vents exhaust outside the home.\r\n<h3>Oil Furnace</h3>\r\nAn oil furnace operates similar to a forced-air furnace, but uses oil that is burned into a fine mist so it can be absorbed into the air and carried to the rooms through ducts.\r\n<h3>Electric Furnace</h3>\r\nThese furnaces use heated coils to warm air that is blown through the system, then distributed to the home through ducts. They are also commonly used with heat pumps and central air conditioners.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps \" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps </a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Systems \" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating-cooling/\">Zone Systems </a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Contact Us Today</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, we have several options for furnaces and furnace service that will fit every home. <strong>Give us a call at <strong>952-641-0099</strong> or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to find out how we can help you with your heating needs.</strong>','Furnaces','','inherit','open','open','','255-revision-v1','','','2013-10-14 13:46:50','2013-10-14 13:46:50','',255,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/255-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(938,1,'2013-10-24 17:29:46','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2013-10-24 17:29:46','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?p=938',0,'post','',0),(939,1,'2013-10-24 17:51:01','2013-10-24 17:51:01','','Air Conditioner','','inherit','open','open','','brands-we-service-4','','','2013-10-24 17:51:01','2013-10-24 17:51:01','',246,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Brands-We-Service2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(590,1,'2013-09-27 18:57:32','2013-09-27 18:57:32','','Ben Franklin Water Heater Service','','inherit','open','open','','bf_plumber_m','','','2013-09-27 18:57:32','2013-09-27 18:57:32','',329,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/bf_plumber_m.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(137,1,'2013-09-30 15:47:47','2013-09-30 15:47:47','<h1>Residential Air Conditioning &amp; Heating Company in Minneapolis</h1>\nWelcome to Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air! As your full service residential heating and air conditioning company in Minneapolis, our top priority is to make sure that your 