ure. It means quality heating products, great service, low prices.</li>\r\n	<li>We believe that if you are truly pleased with our services and products in every way, you will have no need to go anywhere else for your HVAC needs.</li>\r\n	<li>At Blue Ox, we provide our customers with “Comfort to Every Degree.”</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>We are happy to serve our neighbors and friends in the Minneapolis area. Call Blue Ox today at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> for service.</strong>','About','','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:37:22','2013-09-19 17:37:22','',5,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/5-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(254,1,'2013-09-13 19:54:03','2013-09-13 19:54:03',' ','','','publish','open','open','','254','','','2013-10-03 14:27:07','2013-10-03 14:27:07','',5,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?p=254',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(255,1,'2013-09-13 19:55:08','2013-09-13 19:55:08','<h1>Quality Furnace Service</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-951\" title=\"Furnace Installation Service \" alt=\"Furnace Installation Service \" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Furnace-Installation-Service-300x199.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" />A furnace is the last line of defense for your family’s comfort when the temperatures drop in Minneapolis. If you are suffering with an old, inefficient, or broken furnace, we can help. Our experienced technicians provide the highest quality service to repair your existing unit and get it working the way it should, or replace your furnace with a brand new one that provides the right level of warmth for your home.\r\n\r\nThe Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air team has over 200 years of combined experience working with all different types of furnaces, so you get peace of mind knowing that you are getting the best service for all different types of furnaces and heating systems.\r\n<h2>Our Furnace Services</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers a range of services for your furnace, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\"><strong>Furnace repair</strong></a> for all different furnace types.</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\"><strong>Furnace replacement</strong></a> for systems that are older and/or cannot be repaired.</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\"><strong>Furnace maintenance</strong></a> for keeping your unit healthy and working all year long.</li>\r\n	<li><strong><a title=\"Furnace Installation \" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></strong> for new systems.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe start with a full diagnostic analysis of your current system and your home so we can identify the right furnace to fit the space that you have. Even though some people think bigger is better, when it comes to your heating and cooling system, having a furnace that is too large or too small for your home can waste energy and cost you money.\r\n\r\nOur experienced repair and installation technicians can help you find the system that is right for you, and get it installed quickly and easily. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air technicians have all passed background checks, are trained in the latest industry advancements and trends, and equipped with state-of-the-art tools and technology to diagnose and solve your furnace problems.\r\n<h2>How Furnaces Work</h2>\r\nYour furnace heats your home by taking cool air from throughout your home, heating it, then distributing it through a series of ducts. There are three main types of furnaces available today.\r\n<h3>Natural Gas Furnace</h3>\r\nA natural gas furnace, also called a forced-air furnace, pulls cool air from the rooms then passes it through a heat exchanger where the gas ignites a burner inside a combustion chamber. The warm air is distributed back to the rooms through the same duct system, and vents exhaust outside the home.\r\n<h3>Oil Furnace</h3>\r\nAn oil furnace operates similar to a forced-air furnace, but uses oil that is burned into a fine mist so it can be absorbed into the air and carried to the rooms through ducts.\r\n<h3>Electric Furnace</h3>\r\nThese furnaces use heated coils to warm air that is blown through the system, then distributed to the home through ducts. They are also commonly used with heat pumps and central air conditioners.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps \" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps </a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Systems \" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating-cooling/\">Zone Systems </a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Contact Us Today</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, we have several options for furnaces and furnace service that will fit every home. <strong>Give us a call at <strong>952-641-0099</strong> or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to find out how we can help you with your heating needs.</strong>','Furnaces','','publish','open','open','','furnaces','','','2013-10-24 18:05:53','2013-10-24 18:05:53','',6,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=255',0,'page','',0),(256,1,'2013-09-13 19:55:08','2013-09-13 19:55:08','','Furnaces','','inherit','open','open','','255-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 19:55:08','2013-09-13 19:55:08','',255,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/255-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(257,1,'2013-09-13 19:55:19','2013-09-13 19:55:19','<h1>Affordable Furnace Repair</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignright  wp-image-953\" title=\"Furnace Repair \" alt=\"Furnace Repair \" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Heater-Repair-Blue-Ox-214x300.jpg\" width=\"193\" height=\"270\" />When winter comes in Minneapolis, every home needs a furnace that works. If something happens to your furnace system and you need emergency furnace repair, contact the professional at Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air. Our trained technicians have a combined 200 years of experience working with all types of furnaces, and can get you the service you need right away to resolve your heating issues.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating-cooling/\">Zone Systems</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Common Problems with Furnaces</h2>\r\nA furnace is a complex system with a lot of parts that all need to be working in order to provide heat for your home. While there may be hundreds of reasons that your furnace is not working properly, the most common problems that we see are:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Issues with the thermostat that cause the heat or fan to malfunction, or the temperature inside your home to get too hot or too cold.</li>\r\n	<li>Air flow issues caused by worn or broken fan motors, belts, and bearings.</li>\r\n	<li>Filters that are dirty or clogged, restricting air flow and preventing the system from properly heating the air.</li>\r\n	<li>Pilot or ignition problems, which can shut off a heating unit entirely and not allow any warm air through.</li>\r\n	<li>Lack of regular or routine maintenance, resulting in higher energy costs from inefficient operation, and often leading to inconvenient and unexpected system failure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTo prevent problems with your furnace, call our team to provide regular maintenance and check-ups. If you find that you already have a problem, we can help you get the furnace repair done quickly so you don’t have to suffer through the winter months with a broken unit. We take care of gas furnace repair, oil furnace repair, and electric furnace repair.\r\n<h2>Emergency Furnace Repair You Can Count On</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air we offer emergency furnace repairs by qualified, trained technicians. Every member of our team has passed a background check, and is equipped with the latest tools and technology to fix any type of furnace. We also work to ensure our team is up to date with trends in the heating and cooling industry so they can provide the most efficient and effective repairs, and we offer convenient night and weekend appointments, as well as free estimates for new equipment.\r\n\r\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact us</a> today at 952-641-0099 to have one of our trusted furnace repair technicians take a look at your system and find out what needs to be done to restore warmth and comfort to your Minneapolis home.</strong>','Furnace Repair','','publish','open','open','','furnace-repair','','','2013-10-25 16:51:31','2013-10-25 16:51:31','',6,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=257',0,'page','',0),(258,1,'2013-09-13 19:55:19','2013-09-13 19:55:19','','Furnace Repair','','inherit','open','open','','257-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 19:55:19','2013-09-13 19:55:19','',257,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/257-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(259,1,'2013-09-13 19:55:32','2013-09-13 19:55:32','<h1>Furnace Replacement For Damaged Units</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Furnace-Replacement-Services.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-759\" title=\"Furnace Replacement Services\" alt=\"Furnace Replacement Services\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Furnace-Replacement-Services-300x207.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"207\" /></a>A <a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">furnace</a> is a long-term investment designed to last many years, but just like any other appliance, it can wear down over time; when it does, Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air can help you with furnace replacement for your old unit. Maintaining a comfortable and healthy home means having an efficient and effective furnace, and the wrong time to wish you had replaced your furnace is when it fails in the middle of a cold Minneapolis winter night.\r\n\r\nBlue Ox can help assess your current unit to find out if it needs replacement, and identify the furnace replacement cost as well as the timeline to get a new system. If your system is already damaged, we can help you determine whether it would be more beneficial to repair it or go with furnace replacement.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating-cooling/\">Zone Systems</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>When to Repair and When to Replace a Furnace</h2>\r\nSometimes it can be difficult to know whether you should repair your existing furnace or replace it with a new one. Since furnace replacement costs can be high, many homeowners prefer to pay for repairs, but it’s important to know the warning signs that indicate you need a new furnace:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Your furnace is old</strong>. Furnaces that are older than 12-15 years are likely inefficient, and should be replaced before a major problem occurs.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Your monthly utility bills are increasing</strong>. Higher utility bills often indicate an inefficient system that has to run longer to provide the same amount of heat.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>The thermostats are inconsistent</strong>. If you are constantly adjusting the thermostat to try and find the right temperature, the furnace may not be distributing air properly.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>You are spending a lot on repairs</strong>. As a furnace ages, the costs to repair can be expensive, and frequent. Instead of spending more money to repair an inefficient and old furnace, consider getting a new one.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Your furnace is making noises</strong>. While all furnaces make a little bit of noise, excessive noise or strange sounds like banging, popping, and rattling can indicate a problem.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Professional Repairs Offered 24 Hours a Day</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air hires only the highest quality technicians to replace your old furnace. We offer 24-hour repair services for emergency situations and can come to your house any time of the day or night that you experience problems with your furnace. You can rest assured when you hire Blue Ox that our technicians will provide the highest level of customer service and professionalism. Every member of our team has passed a background check and has the proper training and experience to quickly diagnose and resolve issues with all types of furnaces, no matter what time of the day or night.\r\n\r\n<strong>Don’t wait for your old furnace to quit, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us</a> today at 952-641-0099 to get a brand new, energy efficient furnace installed by our team of trained furnace replacement professionals.</strong>','Furnace Replacement','','publish','open','open','','furnace-replacement','','','2013-10-10 16:39:55','2013-10-10 16:39:55','',6,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=259',0,'pag