Ensure that the control valve is open</li>\r\n	<li>Switch out the air filter</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Scheduled Furnace Maintenance Saves You Time</h2>\r\nBe proactive when it comes to your furnace maintenance needs. We recommended that you schedule a planned service appointment with us before the winter season blows in to save yourself some time and possibly even some money.\r\n<h2>Contact Us Today</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air helps the Minneapolis area take care of all of their heating, air and furnace maintenance needs. We offer homeowners night and weekend appointments, 24-hour emergency repair services and specialize in gas furnace maintenance and oil furnace maintenance, electric furnace maintenance, and natural gas furnace maintenance. All of our work is carried out by certified technicians who have undergone background checks, and we offer free estimates on any new equipment that you might need.\r\n\r\n<strong>To schedule furnace maintenance for your home, get in touch with us by calling 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a>.</strong>','Furnace Maintenance','','publish','open','open','','furnace-maintenance','','','2013-10-24 18:39:58','2013-10-24 18:39:58','',6,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=261',0,'page','',0),(262,1,'2013-09-13 19:55:44','2013-09-13 19:55:44','','Furnace Maintenance','','inherit','open','open','','261-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 19:55:44','2013-09-13 19:55:44','',261,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/261-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(263,1,'2013-09-13 19:55:57','2013-09-13 19:55:57','<h1>Furnace Installation Service</h1>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-955 alignright\" title=\"Furnace Installation\" alt=\"Furnace Installation\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Furnace-Repair-and-HVAC-Technician-300x214.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"178\" />Keep warm and cozy this winter season by installing a furnace for your Minneapolis home. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air can offer suggestions for furnace installation, getting the right furnace for your home, and determining how much your installation will cost. We take into consideration all of the factors when helping you to choose and install your new furnace.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating-cooling/\">Zone Systems</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Which Type of Furnace is Right for You?</h2>\r\nWhen you’re deciding what kind of furnace is right for you and your home, you’ll want to start with the type of fuel you want your unit to run on. Your options include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Natural gas</li>\r\n	<li>Propane (LP)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYour decision can be based on your personal preferences or the area in which you live. If your home is located in a more rural area, then a natural gas furnace might not be a viable option for you. If you only have access to liquid propane than you might want to consider an air source <a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">heat pump</a>.\r\n\r\nWe also recommended that you pay attention to how efficient the furnace is before you schedule furnace installation. The higher the furnaces\' efficiency, the lower the monthly cost to operate. Even though you might spend more on a high quality gas furnace installation, you’ll be saving money in the long run.\r\n<h2>How Much Does Furnace Installation Cost?</h2>\r\nThe amount that you’ll have to pay to have your furnace installed will depend on the selected furnace, the amount of labor required for installation, the supplies and materials necessary for installation. Blue Ox offers free estimates on new equipment, so be sure to let us know if you’re interested in new furnace installation.\r\n<h2>Get in Touch with Us Today</h2>\r\nDon’t freeze your way through a Minneapolis winter with an old, unsafe  or malfunctioning furnace. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers comfort to every degree and specializes in  furnace installation. While you’re here at our website, be sure to check out our coupon offers to save yourself even more money. <strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact one of our representatives</a> today by calling 952-641-0099.</strong>','Furnace Installation','','publish','open','open','','furnace-installation','','','2013-10-25 16:50:17','2013-10-25 16:50:17','',6,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=263',0,'page','',0),(264,1,'2013-09-13 19:55:57','2013-09-13 19:55:57','','Furnace Installation','','inherit','open','open','','263-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 19:55:57','2013-09-13 19:55:57','',263,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/263-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(265,1,'2013-09-13 19:56:10','2013-09-13 19:56:10','<h1>Home Heat Exchangers</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Heat-Exchanger.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-834\" title=\"Heat Exchanger\" alt=\"Heat Exchanger\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Heat-Exchanger-300x199.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>Make your home heater more efficient with the use of a home heat exchanger. At Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, we realize how expensive it can be to heat up your home and understand that you want to do everything you can to save money while still keeping warm. A heat exchanger helps to spread or exchange heat throughout your home so that you can be comfortable in every room.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating/\">Zone Heating</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Heat Exchangers Work</h2>\r\nIf you’re using an air-to-air recuperative heat exchanger, both the outgoing and the incoming air is divided by a duct wall or another type of solid barrier. If the temperature between the two air flows has enough difference, the heat from the warmer flow of air is transmitted through the duct wall to the cooler flow of air. If you understand the laws of thermodynamics, then you already know that heat will always shift from a hotter space to a colder space. An air-to-air heat exchanger will benefit you.\r\n\r\nIf you’re using the heat exchanger with a furnace, the process goes as follows:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hot gasses flow into the exchanger</li>\r\n	<li>Air flows over the exterior walls of the air-to-heat exchanger</li>\r\n	<li>Cooled gasses are passed outside</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Advantages to Installing a Heat Exchanger</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air recommends that you invest in a quality heat exchanger because they’re adaptable to different environments, compact, more affordable and easier to clean. One of the biggest advantages of using heat exchangers is that they can work efficiently even at the lowest temperature differences. Something else to think about with a home heat exchanger is that it’s easy to install, so you won’t have to worry about calling to schedule an appointment or paying someone to install your exchanger.\r\n<h2>Let Us to Help You Today</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers the Minneapolis area an extensive amount of knowledge and experience, so be sure to let us be the first to know when you’re thinking about getting an air-to-heat exchanger for your home. <strong>Get in touch with us today by calling our team at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us Online\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a> if you’re ready to experience comfort to every degree.</strong>','Home Heat Exchangers','','publish','open','closed','','heat-exchangers','','','2013-10-24 19:48:05','2013-10-24 19:48:05','',6,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=265',0,'page','',0),(266,1,'2013-09-13 19:56:10','2013-09-13 19:56:10','','Heat Exchangers','','inherit','open','open','','265-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 19:56:10','2013-09-13 19:56:10','',265,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/265-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(267,1,'2013-09-13 19:56:19','2013-09-13 19:56:19','<h1>Heat Pump Service</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignright  wp-image-959\" title=\"Heat pump\" alt=\"Heat pump\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Heat-Pump-200x300.jpg\" width=\"180\" height=\"270\" />No matter how hot or how cold it is outside, a heat pump can help make sure that your home’s central heating and cooling system isn’t working too hard. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers heat pump installation as well as heat pump service. It’s a great idea to think about getting a heat pump for your home if you’re looking for ways to cut back on your heating bills in the winter and your cooling bills in the summer.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating-cooling/\">Zone Systems</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Different Types of Heat Pumps</h2>\r\nYou’ll have several options to choose from when you’re ready to start researching heat pumps for your home. Heat pump options include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Gas heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Electric heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Mini-split heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Geothermal heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Air-source heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Cold climate heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Ductless heat pumps</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAs you’re reading about the different types of heat pumps and learning more about heat pump installation and heat pump service, remember that each type of heat pump comes with its own limitations, disadvantages, and advantages.\r\n<h2>How Heat Pumps Save You Money</h2>\r\nHeat pumps are always shifting warm air from where it’s not needed to where it is needed. During the winter season, heat pumps pull heat from outside your home and deliver it to the inside of your home, and during the summer they pull heat from inside of your home and shift it outside.\r\n\r\nAnother advantage of getting a heat pump is that it only moves heat around rather than actually generating it, which makes it work more efficiently. After your heat pump installation, the unit will run on electricity and save you on fuel consumption.\r\n<h2>Contact Us Today</h2>\r\nIf you already have a pump for your home and are in need of heat pump service, let Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air be the first to know. Before you call to set up a service appointment, make sure you check out our homepage to see if we have any coupons that you can use.\r\n\r\n<strong>Prepare your home for the winter season by calling us at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us Online\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a>.</strong>','Heat Pumps','','publish','open','open','','heat-pumps','','','2013-10-24 18:44:17','2013-10-24 18:44:17','',6,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=267',0,'page','',0),(268,1,'2013-09-13 19:56:19','2013-09-13 19:56:19','','Heat Pumps','','inherit','open','open','','267-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 19:56:19','2013-09-13 19:56:19','',267,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/267-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(269,1,'2013-09-13 19:56:29','2013-09-13 19:56:29','<h1>Zone Heating &amp; Cooling Systems</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Zone-Heating-and-Cooling-Systems.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-836\" title=\"Zone Systems \" alt=\"Zone Systems \" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Zone-Heating-and-Cooling-Systems-200x300.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a>Are you tired of burning up or freezing in your own home because your spouse likes the temperature warm and cozy or Arctic chilly? Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air has the solution to your <a title=\"Thermostats\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/thermostats/\">thermostat</a> dilemma. Zone heating and cooling systems divide your house up into specific areas, allowing you to program the temperature of each zone accordingly.\r\n\r\nOur competent heating and cooling professionals are proud to install, repair, and maintain zone heaters and zone air conditioners for customers in the Minneapolis and Twin Cities areas. Whether your family has trouble agreeing on a comfortable temperature or you have rooms in the home that are unoccupied, zone systems can be a definite benefit to your home.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"h