de the correct service for you.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Call Us Today!</h2>\r\nMake Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air your one-stop-shop-for all other services associated with HVAC in the Twin Cities area. We ‘re ready and waiting to take ownership of your home’s heating and cooling system performance, and we promise that you won’t be disappointed by going with us.\r\n\r\n<strong>Call us at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to schedule an appointment with one of our service professionals today.</strong>','Other Services','','publish','open','open','','other-services','','','2013-10-24 19:50:16','2013-10-24 19:50:16','',0,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=301',0,'page','',0),(302,1,'2013-09-13 20:01:15','2013-09-13 20:01:15','','Other Services','','inherit','open','open','','301-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 20:01:15','2013-09-13 20:01:15','',301,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/301-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(303,1,'2013-09-13 20:01:32','2013-09-13 20:01:32','<h1>Indoor Air Quality Services</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignright  wp-image-807\" alt=\"Air Quality\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Air-Quality-300x287.jpg\" width=\"216\" height=\"206\" />When most people think of potential health risks, they typically don\'t think of poor indoor air quality. However, air quality is not just a concern for people living in crowded cities and industrial centers. As a Minneapolis homeowner, you are also at risk of suffering from the effects of poor home air quality.\r\n\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air can provide you with air quality services and solutions. We can help you with everything from choosing a product to installation. Whether you\'re concerned with allergy prevention, dust allergy prevention, or pollutant removal, we have a number of products that can help you.\r\n<h2>Home Air Quality Products to Improve Health</h2>\r\nThere are various ways to improve air quality throughout your home, which can prevent allergy symptoms and respiratory illnesses. We offer the following proven air quality products:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Humidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/humidifiers/\">Humidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Dehumidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/dehumidifiers/\">Dehumidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA Filters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe whole-home systems that we offer are much more effective at allergy prevention and health protection than individual units that clean the air in one room. Only a centralized system allows you to reach and treat all of the air in your home.\r\n<h2>Some Indoor Air Quality Facts That Might Shock You</h2>\r\nMany people do not realize how harmful poor home air quality can be. According to the American Lung Association, poor air quality indoors can cause headaches, exhaustion, nausea, asthma, lung infections, and even lung cancer. The Environmental Protection Agency, meanwhile, reports these disturbing facts about indoor air quality:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Indoor air can contain two to five times the pollutants than that of outdoor air.</li>\r\n	<li>Pollutant concentrations can be even greater because of high temperatures, humidity, and poor ventilation.</li>\r\n	<li>The average American passes nine out of ten hours indoors.</li>\r\n	<li>One of the five worst environmental health risks is indoor air pollution.</li>\r\n	<li>Pollutants can be worse for children because children breathe more air relative to their size.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMany homeowners never suspect the dangers of poor home air quality. Given how much time a typical person spends inside, it is clear that keeping indoor air quality high is a real health concern.\r\n<h2>Call Us Today</h2>\r\nDon\'t delay bringing the air in your home up to healthy standards. Poor air quality can lead to serious problems if you live with it long enough. <strong>You can learn more about the various air quality products that we offer by calling Blue Ox at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a>.</strong>','Air Quality','','publish','open','open','','indoor-air-quality','','','2013-10-25 16:41:32','2013-10-25 16:41:32','',0,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=303',0,'page','',0),(304,1,'2013-09-13 20:01:32','2013-09-13 20:01:32','','Air Quality','','inherit','open','open','','303-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 20:01:32','2013-09-13 20:01:32','',303,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/303-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(305,1,'2013-09-13 20:01:47','2013-09-13 20:01:47','<h1>Whole House Humidifiers</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignright  wp-image-972\" title=\"Whole House Humidifier\" alt=\"Whole House Humidifier\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Whole-House-Humidifier-200x300.jpg\" width=\"180\" height=\"270\" />Installing a whole house humidifier is one of the best ways to feel comfortable in your home while preventing health problems. Air that is too dry can cause or exacerbate numerous health conditions, and for many Minneapolis homeowners, stationing a few humidifiers around the house just isn\'t enough to have humidity control.\r\n\r\nHomeowners who are tired of feeling sick or uncomfortable in their own homes should call Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air for a whole home humidifier installation. Whole home humidifiers use your existing duct system to deliver soothing, moist air to every room. This can save you money, discomfort, and even health problems.\r\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Indoor Air Quality</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Dehumidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/dehumidifiers/\">Dehumidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA Filters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Controlling the Humidity in Your Home</h2>\r\nMaintaining a comfortable level of humidity in the home can be a challenge. During winter months, when indoor heating reduces the relative humidity of already dry air, spending time indoors can be particularly unpleasant.\r\n\r\nMany people don\'t realize that dry air can cause a number of problems. Dryness makes people perceive the air as being colder than it is, which can lead to a higher heating bill. Dry air can also cause the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Skin dryness and irritation</li>\r\n	<li>Respiratory health problems</li>\r\n	<li>Nose bleeds</li>\r\n	<li>Static electricity and frequent shocks</li>\r\n	<li>Cracks in drywall</li>\r\n	<li>Gaps in wood walls or flooring</li>\r\n	<li>Mold</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn other words, dry air can be damaging to parts of your home as well as your health. A whole home humidifier can help you protect your floors and walls, increase your comfort, and even reduce allergy symptoms.\r\n<h2>How Humidifiers Help Control Seasonal Allergies</h2>\r\nHumidifiers help people who suffer from allergies or asthma breathe more easily. Dry air can irritate the throat and lungs, and worsen allergy symptoms like sore throat and cough. Humidifiers help relieve these symptoms and lessen the likelihood of a sinus infection developing.\r\n\r\nIt is important to find the right level of humidity, and keep your whole house humidifier clean. Otherwise, you could introduce allergens like bacteria or mold spores into the air. When used properly, however, a whole home humidifier can go a long way toward relieving the suffering of people with allergies.\r\n<h2>Find Out More Today</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, our goal is to guarantee your satisfaction and provide you with comfort to every degree. <strong>Give us a call at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to have your whole house humidifier questions answered or to schedule an installation.</strong>','Humidifiers','','publish','open','open','','humidifiers','','','2013-10-24 19:05:05','2013-10-24 19:05:05','',303,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=305',0,'page','',0),(306,1,'2013-09-13 20:01:47','2013-09-13 20:01:47','','Humidifiers','','inherit','open','open','','305-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 20:01:47','2013-09-13 20:01:47','',305,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/305-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(307,1,'2013-09-13 20:02:00','2013-09-13 20:02:00','<h1>Whole House Dehumidifiers</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignright  wp-image-974\" title=\"Blue Ox Heating &amp; Cooling \" alt=\"Blue Ox Heating &amp; Cooling \" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Blue-Ox-Technician-With-Cables-200x300.jpg\" width=\"180\" height=\"270\" />Many Minneapolis homeowners use products like <a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">air purifiers</a> and humidifiers, but are still missing out on the benefits of whole home dehumidifiers. A dehumidifier makes hot summer months more tolerable, but more importantly, it can lessen the presence of allergens and prevent damage to your home.\r\n\r\nYou can trust Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air to handle your whole house dehumidifier installation. The prospect of installing and maintaining a whole-home system may seem daunting, but we can take care of the setup, answer your questions, and ensure that your needs are met. The changes you\'ll enjoy afterward will make the process more than worthwhile.\r\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Indoor Air Quality</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Humidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/humidifiers/\">Humidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA Filters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Dehumidifiers Help Seasonal Allergy Relief</h2>\r\nWhen humidity levels in your home are too high, contaminants and allergens can thrive. We can help you to get better humidity control. Using dehumidifiers to dry out the air creates an environment that is less supportive of:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mold</li>\r\n	<li>Mildew</li>\r\n	<li>Bacteria</li>\r\n	<li>Dust mites</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis is one reason that a whole house dehumidifier is a smart investment. A dehumidifier that works on just one or two rooms won\'t be enough to prevent allergens from growing throughout your home. A whole-home system gives you control over humidity levels and air quality throughout your house.\r\n<h2>Tips for Controlling the Humidity in Your Home</h2>\r\nThere are many warning signs that the humidity level in your home is at an unhealthy level. Some common indicators that indoor air is too humid include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mold or rot</li>\r\n	<li>Musty smells</li>\r\n	<li>Wet spots on walls, floors, or ceilings</li>\r\n	<li>Condensation on glass such as windows or doors</li>\r\n	<li>An increase in pests like insects</li>\r\n	<li>Air that feels heavy or muggy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAlthough these conditions are undesirable, it\'s important not to overcompensate when you start using a home dehumidifier. Air that is too dry can cause problems as well, such as irritating your skin, eyes, throat, and lungs. Dry air can also worsen certain allergy symptoms.\r\n\r\nGenerally, a humidity level below 50% is beneficial, but anything below 35% is too dry. An appropriate balance of moisture is essential if you want to see improvements in your health and the condition of your home.\r\n<h2>Get Expert Help Today</h2>\r\nWe\'re here to answer any questions that you have about whole home dehumidifiers or creating a healthy home air environment. <strong>Give us a call at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to get more information or to order your whole house dehumidifier installation.</strong>','Dehumidifiers','','publish','open','open','','dehumidifiers','','','2013-10-24 19:09:55','2013-10-24 19:09:55','',303,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=307',0,'page','',0),(308,1,'2013-09-13 20:02:00','2013-09-13 20:02:00','','Dehumidifiers','','inherit','open','open','','307-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 20:02:00','2013-09-13 20:02:00','',307,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/307-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(309,1,'2013-09-13 20:02:11','2013-09-13 20:02:11','<h1>Home Air Purifiers</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignright  wp-image-976\" title=\"Air Purifier \" alt=\"Air Purifier \" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Air-Purifier-Service-205x300.jpg\" width=\"185\" height=\"270\" />While you have worked hard to safeguard your home against certain household dangers, there may still be invisible contaminants circulating throughout your air. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air can improve the purity of your space with a quality air cleaner. Our dependable technicians are passionate about improving air quality for the re