/li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA Filters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>We Supply Peace of Mind</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, we understand that you want only the best for your family. With that comes the peace of mind knowing that your children are breathing the cleanest air possible. Let us help you transform your safe haven into a place that is truly safe and pure with an air cleaner.\r\n<h2>Contact Us Today!</h2>\r\nOur friendly staff at Blue Ox is waiting for your call. Whether you need a HEPA air purifier or a UV air purifier, our experts will be able to equip your home with the tools it needs to provide amazing air.\r\n\r\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact us</a> at 952-641-0099 to find out more information on our air purifying services. </strong>','Air Purifiers','','publish','open','open','','air-purifiers','','','2013-10-24 19:13:36','2013-10-24 19:13:36','',303,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=309',0,'page','',0),(310,1,'2013-09-13 20:02:11','2013-09-13 20:02:11','','Air Purifiers','','inherit','open','open','','309-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 20:02:11','2013-09-13 20:02:11','',309,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/309-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(311,1,'2013-09-13 20:02:23','2013-09-13 20:02:23','<h1>Home Air Exchangers</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignright  wp-image-1066\" title=\"Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air\" alt=\"Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Blue-Ox-Van-300x200.jpg\" width=\"270\" height=\"180\" />With the looming threat of environmental pollution and local codes, many homeowners have installed thermal windows, vapor barriers, and improved weather-stripping hoping to keep the conditioned air inside the home while keeping the contaminated air outdoors. All of these improvements, however, can increase your indoor air pollution by an astronomical amount.\r\n<h2>Benefits of a Home Air Exchanger</h2>\r\nThe blockage of outdoor air exchange can result in stale indoor air becoming saturated with bacteria, chemicals, dust, mold, and other contaminants. The fresh air professionals at Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air recommend installing a quality air exchanger to remedy this problem. Basement air exchangers, and a whole house air exchangers can make a difference.\r\n<h2>What an Air Exchanger Does</h2>\r\nMuch as its name implies, air exchangers are used to exchange the air between an outdoor and indoor space. An air exchanger will replenish your indoor air, laden with toxins and particulates, with natural, fresh air from the outside. Quality exchangers will have an air filter attached to ensure the air coming into your home is protected from allergens, dust or pollutants. The experts at Blue Ox can install a new exchanger into your existing air conditioning or heating system, ensuring your home has appropriate air exchange.\r\n<h2>How Air Exchangers Contribute to Better Health</h2>\r\nThe indoor air circulating within your home can be surprisingly polluted. In fact, it can be so dirty that it can cause or aggravate serious conditions, such as asthma, lung infections and other chronic respiratory diseases. Occupants may also suffer from fatigue, dry eyes, headaches, and nasal congestion all due to contaminants in the air. The American Lung Association recommends ventilating your home year round to prevent your in-home air levels from becoming dangerously polluted. Quality air exchangers from Blue Ox Heating and Air can:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Increase the air flow between your outdoor and indoor space.</li>\r\n	<li>Create a clean air environment by replacing stagnant indoor air with fresh outdoor air.</li>\r\n	<li>Reduce the toxins and pollutants in your home.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Indoor Air Quality</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Humidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/humidifiers/\">Humidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Dehumidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/dehumidifiers/\">Dehumidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA Filters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Let us Clean Your Air</h2>\r\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact our experienced team</a> at Blue Ox today at 952-641-0099 for an evaluation of the air in your home.</strong> We are happy to serve our fellow Minneapolis residents, as well as the residents of the Twin Cities area. Our team of professionals works hard to ensure the air you breathe is clean and fresh.','Air Exchangers','','publish','open','open','','air-exchangers','','','2013-10-24 21:09:04','2013-10-24 21:09:04','',303,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=311',0,'page','',0),(312,1,'2013-09-13 20:02:23','2013-09-13 20:02:23','','Air Exchangers','','inherit','open','open','','311-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 20:02:23','2013-09-13 20:02:23','',311,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/311-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(313,1,'2013-09-13 20:02:44','2013-09-13 20:02:44','<h1>HEPA Air Filters</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignright  wp-image-1063\" title=\"Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air\" alt=\"Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Blue-Ox-Heating-Air-Back-of-Van-300x200.jpg\" width=\"270\" height=\"180\" />The percentage of homes with indoor air contamination in Minneapolis is growing. It has truly become an epidemic, contributing to various chronic and acute respiratory conditions. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air has been combating the problem by installing quality HEPA filters to our valued customers. According to the Indoor Air Quality Association, these high efficiency particulate air filters function to remove dangerous contaminates from your home, making the air you breathe safe.\r\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Indoor Air Quality</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Humidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/humidifiers/\">Humidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Dehumidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/dehumidifiers/\">Dehumidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Highest Standard in Air Quality</h2>\r\nOur HEPA filters meet the high standards set by the United States Department of Energy. They remove 99.97% of pollutants measuring 0.3 microns from your indoor air. In fact, high-efficiency particulate air filters are used by medical institutions to capture airborne viral and bacterial organisms circulating through the air. At Blue Ox, we use only the highest quality filtration products available, manufactured by the leading experts in air quality.\r\n<h2>Why Invest in High Quality Filters?</h2>\r\nHave you checked your filter lately? Filters can become clogged and congested with dirt, dust, and other particulates. Not only does this affect the efficiency of the heating and cooling equipment, but it also contributes to poor <a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">air quality</a> within your home.\r\n\r\nHere are just a few reasons why you should consider investing in quality filters:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>They clean the air</strong>. Ensure the air in your home is clean and fresh with a high-quality filter.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>They maximize the efficiency of your heating and cooling system</strong>. Reduce the workload of your furnace and air conditioner by ensuring it has a clean filter at all times.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>They increase the lifespan of your furnace and air conditioner</strong>. Clean, high-quality filters will allow the air to freely flow through your duct-system, and avoid overheating, freezing or other damage from occurring.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>They help to avoid costly repairs</strong>. Clogged filters can result in a frozen evaporator coil and  overheating of the furnace which can shut your entire system down. An investment in a better filter will save you money in the long run.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>We specialize in Providing Clean Air</h2>\r\nOur clean air experts at Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air take pride in supplying fresh air to the homes of our customers. <strong>Call us today at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us Online\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to find out how we can improve the air in your living space with exceptional HEPA filters.</strong>','HEPA','','publish','open','open','','hepa-filters','','','2013-10-24 21:08:09','2013-10-24 21:08:09','',303,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=313',0,'page','',0),(314,1,'2013-09-13 20:02:44','2013-09-13 20:02:44','','HEPA','','inherit','open','open','','313-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 20:02:44','2013-09-13 20:02:44','',313,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/313-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(315,1,'2013-09-13 20:02:54','2013-09-13 20:02:54','<h1>UV Light Purification</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignright  wp-image-984\" title=\"Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air \" alt=\"Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air \" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Blue-Ox-Heating-Air-and-HVAC-Technician-300x200.jpg\" width=\"270\" height=\"180\" />Ultraviolet light purification systems have increased in popularity as one of the most efficient ways to clean the air in your home. The professionals at Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air specialize in bringing this amazing technology to their customers in Minneapolis and Twin Cities. It is our goal to bring our loyal customers comfort to every degree in their living space. This includes providing fresh and clean air to breathe through the use of UV lights and filtration systems.\r\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Indoor Air Quality</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Humidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/humidifiers/\">Humidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Dehumidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/dehumidifiers/\">Dehumidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA Filters</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Ultraviolet Filtration Works</h2>\r\nAn ultraviolet purification system functions as a zapper of pollutants and contamination. As the contaminated air flows through the duct-work, the ultraviolet light destroys the structure of bacteria and other microorganisms. UV lights are used in many medical facilities and labs since they effectively destroy a large percentage of bacteria and viruses.\r\n<h2>Why You Need UV Lights in Your Home</h2>\r\nInstalling a new UV light purification system in your home is simple. Our professional team of experts can add the system to your already existing cooling and heating device or they can incorporate them into your air filtration system. We recommend combining UV lights with our high-quality <a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA filter</a> to maximize the air purity in your home.\r\n\r\nThere are many reasons why UV lights can improve the quality of your home, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>They eradicate up to 99.9% of germs circulating throughout the air in your home.</li>\r\n	<li>They work synergistically with other filtration systems to improve the air quality in your home by nearly 99%.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Find Out More</h2>\r\n<strong>Call Blue Ox Heating and Air today at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> </strong>to find out how we can improve your indoor air quality with a professionally installed ultraviolet filtration system. With over 200 years of combined experience, our experts can help your family enjoy healthy and clean air.','UV Lights','','publish','open','open','','uv-lights','','','2013-10-24 19:21:14','2013-10-24 19:21:14','',303,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=315',0,'page','',0),(316,1,'2013-09-13 20:02:54','2013-09-13 20:02:54','','UV Lights','','inherit','open','open','','315-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 20:02:54','2013-09-13 20:02:54','',315,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/315-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(317,1,'2013-09-13 20:04:11','2013-09-13 20:04:11','<h1>Our Annual Maintenance Program</h1>','Service Plans','','draft','open','closed','','service-plans','','','2013-09-24 17:18:37','2013-09-24 17:18:37','',301,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=317',0,'page','',0),(318,1,'2013-09-13 20:04:11','2013-09-13 20:04:11','','Service Plans','','inherit','open','open','','317-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 20:04:11','2013-09-13 20:04:11','',317,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/317-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(319,1,'2013-09-13 21:15:23','2013-09-13 21:15:23','<h1>Ductwork Construction Services</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Custom-Ductwork.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-772\" title=\"Custom Ductwork\" alt=\"Custom Ductwork\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Custom-Ductwork-200x300.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a>An HVAC system’s efficiency is largely determined on how it fits within a home. Installing a system that is not fit to the unique aspects of your home can be like trying to hammer a square peg into a round hole, and can ultimately cost you up to 40% of the system’s designed efficiency.\r\n\r\nThe ductwork is the backbone of your home’s HVAC system, delivering air from your air conditioner or furnace. It’s this stage of the home heating and cooling process that most influences your system’s energy efficiency. That’s why Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers services in custom ductwork fitting to ensure that your system matches your structure. We do our own ductwork construction after determining how and where tubing and connections will run within your home.\r\n<h2>Our Other Services:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Insulated Duct Systems\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/ductwork-insulation/\">Insulated Duct Systems</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Thermostats\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/thermostats/\">Thermostats</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Plumbing\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/plumbing/\">Plumbing</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Water Heaters\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/water-heaters/\">Water Heaters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality \" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Air Quality </a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Custom Ductwork Saves You Money</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox, we have over 200 years of combined experience in meeting the HVAC needs of the Twin Cities residents. That experience has taught us that a majority of your heating and cooling savings come from not wasting energy by pushing more air through your system to compensate for its design inadequacies.\r\n\r\nThese factors illustrate that point:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Size</strong>: Imagine yourself trying to blow air through a length of PVC pipe. Odds are not much is coming out of the other end. Now imagine doing the same thing with a straw, and you can picture the difference. Ductwork is much the same. Ducts that are too large require more energy to push the air through the system.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Special Connections</strong>: Most energy is lost at junctions in your network of ducts, be it at the plenum, distribution box, or the register. Making sure that these connective ducts fit the contours of the areas they’re placed in helps to cut down on the amount of air lost.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBy allowing us to outfit your home’s HVAC system with custom ductwork, you can avoid the financial pitfalls that can come with choosing a “one-size-fits-all” system not designed to meet your specific heating and cooling needs.\r\n<h2>Trust Us to Help You</h2>\r\nPut our experience in manufacturing custom ductwork to work for you in outfitting your home’s HVAC system. We guarantee that our ductwork construction is second to none, and you’ll feel the results in the new-found comfort you have in your home.\r\n\r\n<strong>Call us at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to schedule an appointment with one of our HVAC technicians today.</strong>','Custom Ductwork','','publish','open','closed','','ductwork-construction','','','2013-10-10 17:25:53','2013-10-10 17:25:53','',301,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=319',0,'page','',0),(320,1,'2013-09-13 21:15:23','2013-09-13 21:15:23','','Custom Ductwork','','inherit','open','open','','319-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 21:15:23','2013-09-13 21:15:23','',319,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/319-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(321,1,'2013-09-13 21:15:46','2013-09-13 21:15:46','<h1>Insulated Duct Systems</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignright  wp-image-986\" title=\"Insulated Duct System \" alt=\"Insulated Duct System \" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Insulated-Duct-System-200x300.jpg\" width=\"180\" height=\"270\" />Your <a title=\"Air Conditioners\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioners/\">air conditioner</a> or furnace is remarkably efficient at doing what what it was designed to do: heating or cooling air. The trick is getting that air into the different rooms of your home for you to enjoy. That’s why your ductwork plays such an integral role in your home’s energy efficiency. Some of the energy in the heated or cooled air is bound to be lost in the transference process. The key is to minimize that loss as much as possible.\r\n\r\nAt Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, we specialize in installing and repairing insulated duct systems that help make sure that your ductwork keeps the conditioned air traveling through your home’s HVAC system as warm or as cool as possible. The ductwork insulation is uniquely designed to fit around the duct tubing itself to provide an extra layer in keeping energy from escaping the system.\r\n<h2>Our Other Services:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Custom Ductwork\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/ductwork-construction/\">Custom Ductwork</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Thermostats\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/thermostats/\">Thermostats</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Plumbing\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/plumbing/\">Plumbing</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Water Heaters\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/water-heaters/\">Water Heaters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality \" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Air Quality </a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Insulated Ductwork Protects Your Home</h2>\r\nOn its own, your <a title=\"Custom Ductwork\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/ductwork-construction/\">duct system</a> is a veritable sieve of warm and cool air. Energy is typically lost through ductwork in three ways:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Heat Conduction</strong>: The US Department of Energy estimates that 10% - 30% of energy used to heat and cool air is lost to conduction through the duct surfaces. Warm air traveling along duct surfaces directly loses heat by contact with the surface. The same process happens with cool air, only with the warmer duct surface heating the cool air.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Radiation</strong>: The energy from heat radiates outward until it reaches a cooler surface, where it is then absorbed by that surface. As that surface then heats, it again radiates the energy outward along a temperature gradient.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Cracks</strong>: After conduction and radiation, cracks along un-insulated ducts are next biggest culprit in energy loss, with an estimated 30% of energy escaping your HVAC system this way.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nInstalling an insulated duct system with Blue Ox is the easiest and most cost-effective way to protect your home from these energy losses. Our technicians know what areas of your system are most at risk for energy loss and thus, where ductwork insulation will be most beneficial.\r\n<h2>Put Our Experts to Work for You</h2>\r\nHelp guarantee your HVAC systems energy efficiency by installing an insulated duct system from Blue Ox. Our team promises to put all of our collective resources to work in ensuring that your ductwork insulation is not only keeping you feeling comfortable in your home, but also allowing you to enjoy the extra savings in your energy costs.\r\n\r\n<strong>Call us at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to speak with one of our service professionals today.</strong>','Insulated Duct Systems','','publish','open','closed','','ductwork-insulation','','','2013-10-24 19:25:46','2013-10-24 19:25:46','',301,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=321',0,'page','',0),(322,1,'2013-09-13 21:15:46','2013-09-13 21:15:46','','Insulated Duct Systems','','inherit','open','open','','321-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 21:15:46','2013-09-13 21:15:46','',321,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/321-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(323,1,'2013-09-13 21:15:55','2013-09-13 21:15:55','<h1>Digital &amp; Programmable Thermostats</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Thermostats.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-783\" title=\"Thermostats\" alt=\"Thermostats\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Thermostats-300x219.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"219\" /></a>You may love the benefits provided by your HVAC system, but not the constant monitoring that goes into making sure that the temperature inside your home is adequate. Unfortunately, your HVAC system is designed to simply generate hot and cold air, not to recognize when it’s needed. It needs someone calling the shots.\r\n\r\nThat someone is the thermostat. Thermostats may be the most overlooked component of an HVAC system, yet could also be the most important given that they regulate the system’s output. And with a programmable thermostat installaton by the professionals at Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, the job of controlling your HVAC system is done for you. At Blue Ox, we offer a wide variety of programmable digital thermostats to take the away the worry of monitoring your system, allowing you to simply enjoy the comfort that it provides.\r\n<h2>WiFi Thermostats Available</h2>\r\nAs more and more people connect to the Internet for services, a new trend is emerging in thermostat design and functionality. Now, many thermostat models come with the capability to connect right to your home\'s WiFi, allowing you greater control over your home\'s heating and cooling needs even when you aren\'t home.\r\n\r\nBlue Ox is proud to offer the following types of WiFi thermostats to homeowners in and around the Twin Cities area:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Honeywell Prestige RedLink\" href=\"http://www.forwardthinking.honeywell.com/products/wireless/wireless_products.html\" target=\"_blank\">Honeywell Prestige RedLink Thermostat</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"FocusPRO 6000 WiFi\" href=\"http://yourhome.honeywell.com/home/Products/Thermostats/5-1-1-Day-Programmable/FocusPRO+6000.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Honeywell FocusPRO 6000 WiFi</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Our Other Services:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Custom Ductwork\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/ductwork-construction/\">Ductwork Construction</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Insulated Duct Systems\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/ductwork-insulation/\">Insulated Duct Systems</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Plumbing\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/plumbing/\">Plumbing</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Water Heaters\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/water-heaters/\">Water Heaters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality \" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Air Quality </a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Advantages of Upgrading Your Thermostat</h2>\r\nIf you’re tired of having to worry about constantly adjusting your thermostat, consider the advantages a programmable one has to offer:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Programming</strong>: You can set your thermostat setting according to time of day and day of week.  That allows for pre-determined settings that automatically change your HVAC output without you having to worry about it.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Savings</strong>: Programmable thermostats have been shown to save homeowners up to $180 per year based on an annual average of $2,200 in home heating and cooling costs. That more than makes up for their initial purchase price.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Design</strong>: Unlike the box-like thermostats that sat as an eyesore on your wall in the past, new programmable thermostats come with backlit display panels that have touchscreen controls.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Digital Thermostats Make Your Life Easier</h2>\r\nDigital thermostats are literally thinking machines that use special thermistors to measure current temperatures compared to preset controls. Whenever the two don’t match, the digital thermostat automatically engages your HVAC system to reach the desired temperature. By taking the few minutes to set up initial programming, you allow the thermostat to monitor and control its own output.\r\n\r\nSome of our most popular digital and programmable thermostats include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"ComfortNet Thermostat\" href=\"http://www.goodmanmfg.com/home/products/controlsthermostats/comfortnetthermostats/tabid/839/default.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Goodman\'s ComfortNet Communicating Control System</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"FocusPRO 6000\" href=\"http://yourhome.honeywell.com/home/Products/Thermostats/5-2-Day-Programmable/FocusPRO+6000.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Honeywell FocusPRO 6000</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"FocusPRO 5000\" href=\"http://yourhome.honeywell.com/home/Products/Thermostats/Digital-Non-Programmable/FocusPRO+5000.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Honeywell FocusPRO 5000</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Call us today at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to speak with an HVAC professional about getting a new digital thermostat today.</strong>','Thermostats','','publish','open','open','','thermostats','','','2013-10-11 18:51:22','2013-10-11 18:51:22','',301,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=323',0,'page','',0),(324,1,'2013-09-13 21:15:55','2013-09-13 21:15:55','','Thermostats','','inherit','open','open','','323-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 21:15:55','2013-09-13 21:15:55','',323,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/323-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(325,1,'2013-09-13 21:17:54','2013-09-13 21:17:54','','Controls','','draft','open','open','','controls','','','2013-09-20 16:18:03','2013-09-20 16:18:03','',301,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?page_id=325',0,'page','',0),(326,1,'2013-09-13 21:17:54','2013-09-13 21:17:54','','Controls','','inherit','open','open','','325-revision-v1','','','2013-09-13 21:17:54','2013-09-13 21:17:54','',