thermostat that cause the heat or fan to malfunction, or the temperature inside your home to get too hot or too cold.</li>\n	<li>Air flow issues caused by worn or broken fan motors, belts, and bearings.</li>\n	<li>Filters that are dirty or clogged, restricting air flow and preventing the system from properly heating the air.</li>\n	<li>Pilot or ignition problems, which can shut off a heating unit entirely and not allow any warm air through.</li>\n	<li>Lack of regular or routine maintenance, resulting in higher energy costs from inefficient operation, and often leading to inconvenient and unexpected system failure.</li>\n</ul>\nTo prevent problems with your furnace, call our team to provide regular maintenance and check-ups. If you find that you already have a problem, we can help you get the furnace repair done quickly so you don’t have to suffer through the winter months with a broken unit. We take care of gas furnace repair, oil furnace repair, and electric furnace repair.\n<h2>Emergency Furnace Repair You Can Count On</h2>\nAt Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air we offer emergency furnace repairs by qualified, trained technicians. Every member of our team has passed a background check, and is equipped with the latest tools and technology to fix any type of furnace. We also work to ensure our team is up to date with trends in the heating and cooling industry so they can provide the most efficient and effective repairs, and we offer convenient night and weekend appointments, as well as free estimates for new equipment.\n\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact us</a> today at 952-641-0099 to have one of our trusted furnace repair technicians take a look at your system and find out what needs to be done to restore warmth and comfort to your Minneapolis home.</strong>','Furnace Repair','','inherit','open','open','','257-autosave-v1','','','2013-10-24 18:08:39','2013-10-24 18:08:39','',257,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/257-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(37