i>\n</ul>\nAs you’re reading about the different types of heat pumps and learning more about heat pump installation and heat pump service, remember that each type of heat pump comes with its own limitations, disadvantages, and advantages.\n<h2>How Heat Pumps Save You Money</h2>\nHeat pumps are always shifting warm air from where it’s not needed to where it is needed. During the winter season, heat pumps pull heat from outside your home and deliver it to the inside of your home, and during the summer they pull heat from inside of your home and shift it outside.\n\nAnother advantage of getting a heat pump is that it only moves heat around rather than actually generating it, which makes it work more efficiently. After your heat pump installation, the unit will run on electricity and save you on fuel consumption.\n<h2>Contact Us Today</h2>\nIf you already have a pump for your home and are in need of heat pump service, let Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air be the first to know. Before you call to set up a service appointment, make sure you check out our homepage to see if we have any coupons that you can use.\n\n<strong>Prepare your home for the winter season by calling us at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us Online\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a>.</strong>','Heat Pumps','','inherit','open','open','','267-autosave-v1','','','2013-10-24 18:41:26','2013-10-24 18:41:26','',267,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/267-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(400,1,'2013-09-17 20:25:37','2013-09-17 20:25:37','No matter how hot or how cold it is outside, a heat pump can help make sure that your home’s central heating and cooling system isn’t working too hard. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers heat pump installation as well as heat pump service. It’s a great idea to think about getting a heat pump for your home if you’re looking for ways to cut back on your heating bills in the winter and your cooling bills in the summer.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-exchangers/\">Heat Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating/\">Zone Heating</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Different Types of Heat Pumps</h2>\r\nYou’ll have several options to choose from when you’re ready to start researching heat pumps for your home. Heat pump options include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Gas heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Electric heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Mini-split heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Geothermal heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Air-source heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Cold climate heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Ductless heat pumps</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAs you’re reading about the different types of heat pumps and learning more about heat pump installation and heat pump service, remember that each type of heat pump comes with its own limitations, disadvantages, and advantages.\r\n<h2>How Heat Pumps Save You Money</h2>\r\nHeat pumps are always shifting warm air from where it’s not need to where it is needed. During the winter season, heat pumps pull heat from outside your home to the inside of your home, and during the summer they pull heat from inside of your home and shift it outside. This allows your air conditioner to work more efficiently without you having to make any adjustments to it.\r\n\r\nAnother advantage of getting a heat pump is that it only moves heat around rather than actually generating it, which makes it work more efficiently. After your heat pump installation, the unit will run on electricity and save you on fuel consumption.\r\n<h2>Contact Us Today</h2>\r\nIf you already have a pump for your home and are in need of heat pump service, let Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air be the first to know. Before you call to set up a service appointment, make sure you check out our homepage to see if we have any coupons that you can use.\r\n\r\n<strong>Prepare your home for the winter season by calling us at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us Online\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a>.</strong>','Heat Pumps','','inherit','open','open','','267-revision-v1','','','2013-09-17 20:25:37','2013-09-17 20:25:37','',267,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/267-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(401,1,'2013-10-11 18:48:47','2013-10-11 18:48:47','<h1>HEPA Air Filters</h1>\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/HEPA.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-820\" alt=\"HEPA\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/HEPA-200x300.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a>The percentage of homes with indoor air contamination in Minneapolis is growing. It has truly become an epidemic, contributing to various chronic and acute respiratory conditions. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air has been combating the problem by installing quality HEPA filters to our valued customers. The Indoor Air quality Associhigh efficiency particulate air filters function to remove dangerous contaminates from your home, making the air you breathe safe.\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\n<ul>\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Indoor Air Quality</a></li>\n	<li><a title=\"Humidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/humidifiers/\">Humidifiers</a></li>\n	<li><a title=\"Dehumidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/dehumidifiers/\">Dehumidifiers</a></li>\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\n	<li><a title=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>The Highest Standard in Air Quality</h2>\nOur HEPA filters meet the high standards set by the United States Department of Energy. They remove 99.97% of pollutants measuring 0.3 microns from your indoor air. In fact, high-efficiency particulate air filters are used by medical institutions to capture airborne viral and bacterial organisms circulating through the air. At Blue Ox, we use only the highest quality filtration products available, manufactured by the leading experts in air quality.\n<h2>Why Invest in High Quality Filters?</h2>\nHave you checked your filter lately? Filters can become clogged and congested with dirt, dust, and other particulates. Not only does this affect the efficiency of the heating and cooling equipment, but it also contributes to poor <a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">air quality</a> within your home.\n\nHere are just a few reasons why you should consider investing in quality filters:\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>They clean the air</strong>. Ensure the air in your home is clean and fresh with a high-quality filter.</li>\n	<li><strong>They maximize the efficiency of your heating and cooling system</strong>. Reduce the workload of your furnace and air conditioner by ensuring it has a clean filter at all times.</li>\n	<li><strong>They increase the lifespan of your furnace and air conditioner</strong>. Clean, high-quality filters will allow the air to freely flow through your duct-system, and avoid overheating, freezing or other damage from occurring.</li>\n	<li><strong>They help to avoid costly repairs</strong>. Clogged filters can result in a frozen evaporator 