le=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA Filters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe whole-home systems that we offer are much more effective at allergy prevention and health protection than individual units that clean the air in one room. Only a centralized system allows you to reach and treat all of the air in your home.\r\n<h2>Some Indoor Air Quality Facts That Might Shock You</h2>\r\nMany people do not realize how harmful poor home air quality can be. According to the American Lung Association, poor air quality indoors can cause headaches, exhaustion, nausea, asthma, lung infections, and even lung cancer. The Environmental Protection Agency, meanwhile, reports these disturbing facts about indoor air quality:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Indoor air can contain two to five times the pollutants that outdoor air does.</li>\r\n	<li>Pollutant concentrations can be even greater because of high temperatures, humidity, and poor ventilation.</li>\r\n	<li>The average American passes nine out of ten hours indoors.</li>\r\n	<li>One of the five worst environmental health risks is indoor air pollution.</li>\r\n	<li>Pollutants can be worse for children because children breathe more air relative to their size.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMany homeowners never suspect the dangers of poor home air quality. Given how much time a typical person spends inside, it is clear that keeping indoor air quality high is a real health concern.\r\n<h2>Call Us Today</h2>\r\nDon\'t delay bringing the air in your home up to healthy standards. Poor air quality can lead to serious problems if you live with it long enough. <strong>You can learn more about the various air quality products that we offer by calling Blue Ox at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a>.</strong>','Air Quality','','inherit','open','open','','303-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:42:13','2013-09-19 17:42:13','',303,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/303-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(479,1,'2013-09-19 17:42:41','2013-09-19 17:42:41','<h1>Home Air Exchangers</h1>\r\nWith the looming threat of environmental pollution, many homeowners have installed thermal windows, vapor barriers, and improved weather-stripping hoping to keep the contaminated air outdoors. All of these improvements, however, can increase your indoor air pollution by an astronomical amount. The blockage of air exchange can result in stale indoor air becoming saturated with bacteria, chemicals, dust, mold, and other contaminants. The fresh air professionals at Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air recommend installing a quality air exchanger to remedy this problem.\r\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Indoor Air Quality</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Humidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/humidifiers/\">Humidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Dehumidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/dehumidifiers/\">Dehumidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA Filters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>What an Air Exchanger Does</h2>\r\nMuch as its name implies, air exchangers are used to exchange the air between an outdoor and indoor space. An air exchanger will replenish your indoor air, laden with toxins and particulates, with natural, fresh air from the outside. Quality exchangers will have an air filter attached to ensure the air coming into your home is free from allergens, dust or pollutants. The experts at Blue Ox can install a new exchanger into your existing air conditioning or heating system, ensuring your home has appropriate air exchange.\r\n<h2>How Air Exchangers Contribute to Better Health</h2>\r\nThe indoor air circulating within your home can be surprisingly polluted. In fact, it can be so dirty that it can cause or aggravate serious conditions, such as asthma, lung infections and other chronic respiratory diseases. Occupants may also suffer from fatigue, dry eyes, headaches, and nasal congestion all due to contaminants in the air. The American Lung Association recommends ventilating your home year round to prevent your in-home air levels from becoming dangerously polluted. Quality air exchangers from Blue Ox Heating and Air can:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Increase the air flow between your outdoor and indoor space.</li>\r\n	<li>Create a clean air environment by replacing your stagnant indoor air with fresh outdoor air.</li>\r\n	<li>Reduce the toxins and pollutants in your home.</li>\r\n	<li>Help the efficiency of your heating and cooling system.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Let us Clean Your Air</h2>\r\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact our experienced team</a> at Blue Ox today at 952-647-0099 for an evaluation of the air in your home.</strong> We are happy to serve our fellow Minneapolis residents, as well as the residents of the Twin Cities area. Our team of professionals works hard to ensure the air you breathe is clean and fresh.','Air Exchangers','','inherit','open','open','','311-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:42:41','2013-09-19 17:42:41','',311,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/311-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(480,1,'2013-09-19 17:42:58','2013-09-19 17:42:58','<h1>Home Air Purifiers</h1>\r\nWhile you have worked hard to safeguard your home against certain household dangers, there may still be invisible contaminants circulating throughout your air