We specialize in providing the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HEPA Air Purifiers</li>\r\n	<li>UV Air Purifiers</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWith a simple in-home evaluation, our technicians can determine which type of air cleaner will be most beneficial for your family.\r\n<h2>We Supply Peace of Mind</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, we understand that you want only the best for your family. With that comes the peace of mind knowing that your children are breathing the cleanest air possible. Let us help you transform your safe haven into a place that is truly safe and pure with an air cleaner.\r\n<h2>Contact Us Today!</h2>\r\nOur friendly staff at Blue Ox is waiting for your call. Whether you need a HEPA air purifier or a UV air purifier, our experts will be able to equip your home with the tools it needs to provide amazing air.\r\n\r\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact us</a> at 952-647-0099 to find out more information on our air purifying services. </strong>','Air Purifiers','','inherit','open','open','','309-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:42:58','2013-09-19 17:42:58','',309,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/309-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(481,1,'2013-09-19 17:43:12','2013-09-19 17:43:12','<h1>Whole House Dehumidifiers</h1>\r\nMany Minneapolis homeowners use products like <a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">air purifiers</a> and humidifiers, but are still missing out on the benefits of whole home dehumidifiers. A dehumidifier makes hot summer months more tolerable, but more importantly, it can lessen the presence of allergens and prevent damage to your home.\r\n\r\nYou can trust Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air to handle your whole house dehumidifier installation. The prospect of installing and maintaining a whole-home system may seem daunting, but we can take care of the setup, answer your questions, and ensure that your needs are met. The changes you\'ll enjoy afterward will make the process more than worthwhile.\r\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Indoor Air Quality</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Humidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/humidifiers/\">Humidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA Filters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Dehumidifiers Help Seasonal Allergy Relief</h2>\r\nWhen humidity levels in your home are too high, contaminants and allergens can thrive. Using dehumidifiers to dry out the air creates an environment that is less supportive of:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mold</li>\r\n	<li>Mildew</li>\r\n	<li>Bacteria</li>\r\n	<li>Dust mites</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis is one reason that a whole house dehumidifier is a smart investment. A dehumidifier that works on just one or two rooms won\'t be enough to prevent allergens from growing throughout your home. A whole-home system gives you control over humidity levels and air quality throughout your house.\r\n<h2>Tips for Controlling the Humidity in Your Home</h2>\r\nThere are many warning signs that the humidity level in your home is at an unhealthy level. Some common indicators that indoor air is too humid include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mold or rot</li>\r\n	<li>Musty smells</li>\r\n	<li>Wet spots on walls, floors, or ceilings</li>\r\n	<li>Condensation on glass such as windows or doors</li>\r\n	<li>An increase in pests like insects</li>\r\n	<li>Air that feels heavy or muggy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAlthough these conditions are undesirable, it\'s important not to overcompensate when you start using a dehumidifier. Air that is too dry can cause problems as well, such as irritating your skin, eyes, throat, and lungs. Dry air can also worsen certain allergy symptoms.\r\n\r\nGenerally, a humidity level below 50% is beneficial, but anything below 35% is too dry. An appropriate balance of moisture is essential if you want to see improvements in your health and the condition of your home.\r\n<h2>Get Expert Help Today</h2>\r\nWe\'re here to answer any questions that you have about whole home dehumidifiers or creating a healthy home air environment. <strong>Give us a call at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to get more information or to order your whole house dehumidifier installation.</strong>','Dehumidifiers','','inherit','open','open','','307-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:43:12','2013-09-19 17:43:12','',307,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/307-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(482,1,'2013-09-19 17:43:26','2013-09-19 17:43:26','<h1>HEPA Air Filters</h1>\r\nThe percentage of indoor air contamination in Minneapolis is growing. It has truly become an epidemic, contributing to various chronic and acute respiratory conditions. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air has been combating the problem by installing quality HEPA filters to our valued customers. These high efficiency particulate air filters function to remove dangerous contaminates from your home, making the air you breathe safe.\r\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Indoor Air Quality</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Humidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/humidifiers/\">Humidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Dehumidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/dehumidifiers/\">Dehumidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Highest Standard in Air Quality</h2>\r\nOur HEPA filters meet the high standards set by the United States Department of Energy. They remove 99.97% of pollutants measuring 0.3 microns from your indoor air. In fact, high-efficiency particulate air filters are used by medical institutions to capture airborne viral and bacterial organisms circulating through the air. At Blue Ox, we use only the highest quality filtration products available, manufactured by the leading experts in air quality.\r\n<h2>Why Invest in High Quality Air Conditioner Filters?</h2>\r\nHave you checked your air conditioner filter lately? Air conditioner filters can become clogged and congested with dirt, dust, and other particulates. Not only does this affect the efficiency of the air conditioner, but it also contributes to poor <a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">air quality</a> within your home.\r\n\r\nHere are just a few reasons why you should consider investing in quality air conditioner filters:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>They clean the air</strong>. Ensure the air in your home is clean and fresh with a high-quality filter.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>They maximize the efficiency of your air conditioning unit</strong>. Reduce the workload of your air conditioning unit by ensuring it has a clean filter at all times.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>They increase the lifespan of your air conditioner</strong>. Clean, high-quality filters will allow the air to freely flow through your air conditioner, and avoid overheating or other damage from occurring.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>They help to avoid costly air conditioner repairs</strong>. Clogged filters can result in a frozen evaporator coil, which can shut your entire cooling system down. An investment in a better filter will definitely save you money in the long run.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>We specialize in Providing Clean Air</h2>\r\nOur clean air experts at Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air take pride in supplying fresh air to the homes of our customers. <strong>Call us today at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us Online\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to find out how we can improve the air in your living space with exceptional HEPA filters.</strong>','HEPA','','inherit','open','open','','313-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:43:26','2013-09-19 17:43:26','',313,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/313-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(483,1,'2013-09-19 17:43:47','2013-09-19 17:43:47','<h1>UV Light Filtration</h1>\r\nUltraviolet light filtration systems have increased in popularity as one of the most efficient ways to clean the air in your home. The professionals at Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air specialize in bringing this amazing technology to their customers in Minneapolis and Twin Cities. It is our goal to bring our loyal customers comfort to every degree in their living space. This includes providing fresh and clean air to breathe through the use of UV lights and filtration systems.\r\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Indoor Air Quality</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Humidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/humidifiers/\">Humidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Dehumidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/dehumidifiers/\">Dehumidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA Filters</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Ultraviolet Filtration Works</h2>\r\nAn ultraviolet filtration system functions as a zapper of pollutants and contamination. As the contaminated air flows through the filter, the ultraviolet light destroys the structure of bacteria and other microorganisms. UV lights are used in many medical facilities and labs since they effectively destroy a large percentage of bacteria and viruses.\r\n<h2>Why You Need UV Lights in Your Home</h2>\r\nInstalling a new UV light filtration system in your home is simple. Our professional team of experts can add the system to your already existing cooling and heating device or they can incorporate them into your air filtration system. We recommend combining UV lights with our high-quality <a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA filter</a> to maximize the air purity in your home.\r\n\r\nThere are many reasons why UV lights can improve the quality of your home, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>They eradicate up to 99.9% of germs circulating throughout the air in your home.</li>\r\n	<li>They work synergistically with other filtration systems to improve the air quality in your home by nearly 99%.</li>\r\n	<li>They help to increase the efficiency of your heating and cooling system by removing filter-clogging contaminants.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Find Out More</h2>\r\n<strong>Call Blue Ox Heating and Air today at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to find out how we can improve your indoor air quality with a professionally installed ultraviolet filtration system.</strong> With over 200 years of combined experience, our experts can help your family enjoy healthy and clean air.','UV Lights','','inherit','open','open','','315-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:43:47','2013-09-19 17:43:47','',315,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/315-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(484,1,'2013-09-19 17:44:03','2013-09-19 17:44:03','<h1>Whole House Humidifiers</h1>\r\nInstalling a whole house humidifier is one of the best ways to feel comfortable in your home while preventing health problems. Air that is too dry can cause or exacerbate numerous health conditions, and for many Minneapolis homeowners, stationing a few humidifiers around the house just isn\'t enough.\r\n\r\nHomeowners who are tired of feeling sick or uncomfortable in their own homes should call Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air for a whole home humidifier installation. Whole home humidifiers use your existing duct system to deliver soothing, moist air to every room. This can save you money, discomfort, and even health problems.\r\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Indoor Air Quality</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Dehumidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/dehumidifiers/\">Dehumidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA Filters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Controlling the Humidity in Your Home</h2>\r\nMaintaining a comfortable level of humidity in the home can be a challenge. During winter months, when indoor heating reduces the relative humidity of already dry air, spending time indoors can be particularly unpleasant.\r\n\r\nMany people don\'t realize that dry air can cause a number of problems. Dryness makes people perceive the air as being colder than it is, which can lead to a higher heating bill. Dry air can also cause the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Skin dryness and irritation</li>\r\n	<li>Respiratory health problems</li>\r\n	<li>Nose bleeds</li>\r\n	<li>Static electricity and frequent shocks</li>\r\n	<li>Cracks in drywall</li>\r\n	<li>Gaps in wood walls or flooring</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn other words, dry air can be damaging to parts of your home as well as your health. A whole home humidifier can help you protect your floors and walls, increase your comfort, and even reduce allergy symptoms.\r\n<h2>How Humidifiers Help Control Seasonal Allergies</h2>\r\nHumidifiers help people who suffer from allergies or asthma breathe more easily. Dry air can irritate the throat and lungs, and worsen allergy symptoms like sore throat and cough. Humidifiers relieve these symptoms and lessen the likelihood of a sinus infection developing.\r\n\r\nIt is important to find the right level of humidity, and keep your whole house humidifier clean. Otherwise, you could introduce allergens like bacteria or mold spores into the air. When used properly, however, a whole home humidifier can go a long way toward relieving the suffering of people with allergies.\r\n<h2>Find Out More Today</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, our goal is to guarantee your satisfaction and provide you with comfort to every degree. <strong>Give us a call at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to have your whole house humidifier questions answered or to schedule an installation.</strong>','Whole House Humidifiers','','inherit','open','open','','305-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:44:03','2013-09-19 17:44:03','',305,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/305-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(489,1,'2013-09-19 17:46:16','2013-09-19 17:46:16','<h1>Seasonal Air Conditioner Maintenance</h1>\r\nAt Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air we are proud to offer exceptional air conditioner maintenance services to those in Minneapolis, MN, and the Twin Cities area. Frequent upkeep of your residential or commercial air conditioner is crucial in order to extend the life of the system and ensure that it is consistently cost-efficient. We strive to preserve our reputation as a company that puts our clients’ comfort first, and our friendly technicians are trained to handle all of your AC maintenance needs, 24/7.\r\n<h2>Our Other Cooling Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioners\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioners/\">Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-repair/\">Air Conditioner Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-installation/\">Air Conditioner Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"High Velocity Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/high-velocity-air-conditioners/\">High Velocity Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Ductless Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/ductless/\">Ductless Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/zone-cooling/\">Zone Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Air Conditioner Maintenance You Can Do at Home</h2>\r\nWhile routine, professional assessments of your HVAC unit are essential in order to safeguard that your system will effectively operate during the warmer months, proper air conditioner maintenance starts at home. The following tips can be used to help maintain your system:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Change Filter</strong> – Dirt can build up in the system if the filters aren’t changed frequently. For those with allergies or asthma, it is best to change the filter every month. For homeowners or businesses without pets, the filter can be replaced every 90 days. A clean filter will promote better air quality and a more efficient system.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Clean Vents</strong> – Warm air is drawn in and cooled through the vents. Over time dust will settle on them and should be cleaned off several times a year.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Brush Condenser Coil</strong> – A clean condenser coil produces cooler air while using less energy. Sometime in the spring, use a vacuum or brush to clean the condenser. Contact an AC maintenance technician if you are unsure how to properly perform this step.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Replace Freon</strong> – Most <a title=\"Air Conditioners\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioners/\">air conditioners</a> don’t require the replacement of Freon but it is still important to check the levels to make sure that there is not a leak in the air conditioner.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf your system is performing erratically or you aren’t comfortable with doing systematic air conditioner maintenance on your own, Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air will be pleased to assist you.\r\n<h2>Scheduled AC Maintenance Saves You Time</h2>\r\nAir conditioner emergencies pop up when you least expect them and usually when they are most inconvenient. Regular maintenance of your air conditioning unit keeps you in control of your schedule and helps you catch minor issues before they become a threat to your time and money.\r\n\r\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact Blue Ox</a> by calling 952-647-0099 to schedule your AC maintenance today.</strong>','Air Conditioner Maintenance','','inherit','open','open','','278-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:46:16','2013-09-19 17:46:16','',278,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/278-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(491,1,'2013-09-19 17:46:41','2013-09-19 17:46:41','<h1>Air Conditioner Units</h1>\r\nThere is nothing like enjoying a hot summer day from the comfort of your air conditioned home. At Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, we sell only the finest quality air conditioner units from the best manufacturers in the business. Our 200 years of combined experience in the business of heating and cooling makes us the best candidates for all of your cooling needs.\r\n<h2>Our Air Conditioner Services</h2>\r\nOur dependable team of professionals is available to service your air conditioners 24 hours a day, seven days a week. Blue Ox specializes in:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-repair/\">Air Conditioner Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-installation/\">Air Conditioner Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-maintenance/\">Air Conditioner Maintenance</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe are so confident in our services that we guarantee your complete satisfaction in everything we do.\r\n<h2>Our Other Cooling Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"High Velocity Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/high-velocity-air-conditioners/\">High Velocity Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Ductless Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/ductless/\">Ductless Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/zone-cooling/\">Zone Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Air Conditioners Work</h2>\r\nAs you sit in your cool house, your air conditioner units are working to direct the hot air from within your home back to the outside. The cool air blowing out of your vents is created as the air conditioning unit sends warm air over the evaporator coil. The evaporator coil consists of a series of cold pipes that are filled with refrigerant. As the refrigerant absorbs heat from the passing air, it turns into a gas. It then moves outside the house, gives up its heat, and returns to a liquid state. A compressor is responsible for moving the refrigerant between the coils and is powered by a motor. Amazingly, this entire process is able to function to bring us the cool and refreshing air that we crave on a hot day.\r\n<h2>Licensed Professionals</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox Heating and Air, we are proud of our highly-skilled team of professionals. Each technician undergoes a rigorous background check before being hired onto the team. We work hard to uphold our exceptional reputation as being the finest heating and cooling company in the Twin Cities and Minneapolis areas. Let our trained team install your air conditioner units today.\r\n<h2>We Provide Comfort to Every Degree</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, we believe that you have the right to feel comfortable in your home. We strive to provide you the best heating and cooling services available. <strong>Call us today at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> for a free evaluation of your air conditioners.</strong>','Air Conditioners','','inherit','open','open','','272-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:46:41','2013-09-19 17:46:41','',272,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/272-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(492,1,'2013-09-19 17:46:55','2013-09-19 17:46:55','<h1>Ductless Air Conditioners</h1>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air understands that keeping your family cool in Minneapolis, MN, is a top priority. Our service professionals also appreciate the fact that every property has unique needs and sometimes a central air conditioning system is not an option.\r\n\r\nWe install ductless air conditioning systems, also referred to as mini-split systems, in homes that require directed air flow without the addition of ducts. A ductless air conditioner is comprised of the outside condenser, the indoor unit (which is mounted on the ceiling or wall, or can remain freestanding), and refrigerant lines that connect the two. It is a compact, easy to install system that is a great choice for any homeowner.\r\n<h2>Our Other Cooling Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioners\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioners/\">Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-repair/\">Air Conditioner Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-installation/\">Air Conditioner Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-maintenance/\">Air Conditioner Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"High Velocity Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/high-velocity-air-conditioners/\">High Velocity Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/zone-cooling/\">Zone Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Advantages of Ductless Air Conditioners</h2>\r\nIf you live in a home that does not have forced air or use ducts, then a central air conditioning system would probably be prohibitively expensive to install. A ductless air cooling unit offers the following great benefits:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Space Saver</strong> – The compact design of a mini-split system makes them ideal for small spaces like apartments, dorm rooms, attics or basements.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Conveniently Operated</strong> – Most of the ductless air conditioner units come with a remote control so that complete management of the room’s temperature is always within reach.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Runs Quietly</strong> – A mini-split unit provides comfort with a strong but quiet performance.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Ductless Mini Split Systems Are Energy Efficient</h2>\r\nA ductless air conditioning system uses less power than a conventional HVAC unit, saving you money in energy costs. If you use a mini-split system, even in conjunction with a conventional ducted air conditioner, you can have better control over which rooms to cool. Energy efficiency is further increased if you find that you are constantly cooling a space that gets little to no use. It is also valuable if your ducted system inefficiently creates hot spots in one area of the house.\r\n<h2>Contact a Skilled Air Conditioning Tech</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air is your trusted source for ductless air conditioner installation and repair services. We fully guarantee our work and ensure complete customer satisfaction with every visit. <strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact us</a> today by calling 952-647-0099</strong>.','Ductless Air Conditioners','','inherit','open','open','','282-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:46:55','2013-09-19 17:46:55','',282,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/282-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(685,1,'2013-10-03 14:29:48','2013-10-03 14:29:48','<h1>High Velocity Air Conditioners</h1>\r\nThe technicians at Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air are experts in the field and understand the intricacies of the weather in Minneapolis, MN, and the Twin Cities area. We keep up to date on the newest systems available and are always prepared to offer property owners the best service possible.\r\n<h2>Our Other Cooling Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioners\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioners/\">Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-repair/\">Air Conditioner Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-installation/\">Air Conditioner Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-maintenance/\">Air Conditioner Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Ductless Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/ductless/\">Ductless Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How High Velocity Air Conditioning Works</h2>\r\nA high velocity air conditioner draws air over cooling coils instead of pushing it like traditional AC units do. Most mini-duct units use coils with a large surface area which creates colder air currents, thus reducing the costs of running the system while also increasing efficiency.\r\n\r\nConsider the benefits of using a high velocity unit in your property:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Consistent Airflow</strong> – The circulation system of a high velocity AC system is designed to create even airflow in every room of the house. They generally come with many vents that are appropriately placed throughout the property to better facilitate those efforts.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Fast &amp; Efficient</strong> – Using half of the airflow of a conventional AC unit, a high velocity air conditioner can quickly cool a room. They also typically eliminate around 30 percent more of the air’s moisture than a standard system can.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Smaller Ducts</strong> – Mini-duct air conditioners don’t require extensive renovation or bulky ducts. This is a benefit for those who have older homes without an existing central HVAC unit, as well as homeowners who cannot afford the high costs of renovating their home to accommodate them.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Making the Switch to High Velocity Air Conditioning is Easy</h2>\r\nSwitching from a conventional HVAC unit to a mini-duct cooling system is easy. The small ducts are only two inches in diameter and can fit easily inside walls and below floors or other tight spaces. Therefore, it is not necessary to build soffits or creative hiding places to conceal metal ductwork, thus maintaining the integrity of your home.\r\n\r\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air</a> today at 952-641-0099 to speak with an air conditioning professional to gain more insight on the benefits of installing a high velocity air conditioner in your home.</strong>','High Velocity Cooling','','inherit','open','open','','280-revision-v1','','','2013-10-03 14:29:48','2013-10-03 14:29:48','',280,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/280-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(493,1,'2013-09-19 17:47:08','2013-09-19 17:47:08','<h1>High Velocity Air Conditioners</h1>\r\nThe technicians at Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air are experts in the field and understand the intricacies of the weather in Minneapolis, MN, and the Twin Cities area. We keep up to date on the newest systems available and are always prepared to offer property owners the best service possible.\r\n<h2>Our Other Cooling Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioners\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioners/\">Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-repair/\">Air Conditioner Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-installation/\">Air Conditioner Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-maintenance/\">Air Conditioner Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Ductless Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/ductless/\">Ductless Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/zone-cooling/\">Zone Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How High Velocity Air Conditioning Works</h2>\r\nA high velocity air conditioner, or mini-duct air conditioner, draws air over cooling coils instead of pushing it like traditional AC units do. Most mini-duct units use coils with a large surface area which creates colder air currents, thus reducing the costs of running the system while also increasing efficiency.\r\n\r\nConsider the benefits of using a high velocity unit in your property:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Consistent Airflow</strong> – The circulation system of a high velocity AC system is designed to create even airflow in every room of the house. They generally come with many vents that are appropriately placed throughout the property to better facilitate those efforts.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Fast &amp; Efficient</strong> – Using half of the airflow of a conventional AC unit, a high velocity air conditioner can quickly cool a room. They also typically eliminate around 30 percent more of the air’s moisture than a standard system can.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Smaller Ducts</strong> – Mini-duct air conditioners don’t require extensive renovation or bulky ducts. This is a benefit for those who have older homes without an existing central HVAC unit, as well as homeowners who cannot afford the high costs of renovating their home to accommodate them.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Making the Switch to High Velocity Air Conditioning is Easy</h2>\r\nSwitching from a conventional HVAC unit to a mini-duct cooling system is easy. The small ducts are only two inches in diameter and can fit easily inside walls and below floors or other tight spaces. Therefore, it is not necessary to build soffits or creative hiding places to conceal metal ductwork, thus maintaining the integrity of your home.\r\n\r\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air</a> today at 952-647-0099 to speak with an air conditioning professional to gain more insight on the benefits of installing a high velocity air conditioner in your home.</strong>','High Velocity Cooling','','inherit','open','open','','280-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:47:08','2013-09-19 17:47:08','',280,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/280-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(494,1,'2013-09-19 17:47:23','2013-09-19 17:47:23','<h1>Zone Air Conditioners</h1>\r\nMany Minneapolis homeowners don\'t realize that they can save money while making their homes more comfortable by installing zone air conditioning. Zone air conditioners control the temperature in every room, so that homeowners don\'t have to over-cool part of the home to make the temperature in another area merely tolerable.\r\n\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air can help you ensure comfort to every degree by installing a zone cooling system. We always aim for 100% customer satisfaction, and we know that you\'ll love the difference in home atmosphere that a zone air conditioner creates.\r\n<h2>Our Other Cooling Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioners\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioners/\">Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-repair/\">Air Conditioner Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-installation/\">Air Conditioner Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-maintenance/\">Air Conditioner Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"High Velocity Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/high-velocity-air-conditioners/\">High Velocity Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Ductless Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/ductless/\">Ductless Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Zone Air Conditioners Work</h2>\r\nZone air conditioners use a <a title=\"Thermostats\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/thermostats/\">thermostat</a> in each room to open or close dampers inside the air conditioning ductwork. These dampers determine the amount of cold air that enters each room. It makes sense to set up separate room thermostats because temperatures can vary between rooms based on many factors, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Exposure to sunlight</li>\r\n	<li>Presence of windows and doors</li>\r\n	<li>Level of the house that the room is located on</li>\r\n	<li>Presence of heating appliances or other heat sources</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nZone air conditioning can help homeowners keep the entire house at a consistent temperature. Zone cooling is also the best solution for homeowners who want distinct temperatures in different rooms.\r\n<h2>Zone Cooling Helps You Save on Monthly Bills</h2>\r\nHot and humid summers cause many Minneapolis homeowners to spend more than they like on their electric bills. With a zone cooling system, however, you won\'t have to choose between saving money and being comfortable.\r\n\r\nZone air conditioners allow you to cool the rooms that you use and leave the others as they are, reducing energy use. With a typical air conditioning system, you would have to manually close vents in rooms that don\'t need cooling, which is ineffective and can damage your ducts over time. Zone cooling is a much more reliable, cost-effective approach for homeowners who want to keep bills manageable without suffering through summer.\r\n<h2>Start Saving Today</h2>\r\nOnce you begin using zone air conditioning, the energy savings will start offsetting the purchasing price, so there\'s no reason to put off enjoying a better quality of life at home. <strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact Blue Ox</a> by calling 952-647-0099 to get more information or set up an appointment.</strong>','Zone Cooling','','inherit','open','open','','284-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:47:23','2013-09-19 17:47:23','',284,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/284-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(495,1,'2013-09-30 20:13:07','2013-09-30 20:13:07','<h1>Heating &amp; Cooling Financing Plans</h1>\nNot only does Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air have more than 200 years of air conditioning experience, we also offer great financing plans for repair or installation projects. We understand that sometimes repairs to your furnace or air conditioner can come as a shock, and there’s no reason for you to be stuck in the sweltering heat or the bitter cold just because you don’t have the funds to take care of the necessary repair or installation.\n<h2>Financing Details</h2>\nWe offer all of our Minneapolis customers financing in any dollar amount though several sources. Other details of our 