le you’re here at our website, be sure to check out our coupon offers to save yourself even more money. <strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact one of our representatives</a> today by calling 952-641-0099.</strong>','Furnace Installation','','inherit','open','open','','263-revision-v1','','','2013-10-24 19:44:12','2013-10-24 19:44:12','',263,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/263-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(498,1,'2013-09-19 17:48:47','2013-09-19 17:48:47','<h1>Furnace Installation Service</h1>\r\nKeep warm and cozy this winter season by installing a furnace for your Minneapolis home. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air can offer suggestions for furnace installation, getting the right furnace for your home, and determining how much electric or gas furnace installation will cost.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-exchangers/\">Heat Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating/\">Zone Heating</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Which Type of Furnace is Right for You?</h2>\r\nWhen you’re deciding what kind of furnace is right for you and your home, you’ll want to start with the type of fuel you want your unit to run on. Your options include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Natural gas</li>\r\n	<li>Oil</li>\r\n	<li>Electric</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYour decision can be based on your personal preferences or the area in which you live. If your home is located in a more rural area, then an electric furnace might not be a viable option for you. If you have central air, then you’ll probably be better off with a gas or oil furnace or even an electric <a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">heat pump</a>.\r\n\r\nWe also recommended that you pay attention to how efficient the furnace is before you schedule furnace installation. The higher the furnace’s efficiency, the better it works and the less money you have to spend. Even though you might spend more on a high quality gas furnace installation, you’ll be saving money in the long run.\r\n<h2>How Much Does Furnace Installation Cost?</h2>\r\nThe amount that you’ll have to pay to have your furnace installed will depend on the actual cost of the unit, the amount of labor required for installation, the supplies and materials necessary for installation, and the type of equipment that’s used for proper installation. Blue Ox offers free estimates on new equipment, so be sure to let us know if you’re interested in new furnace installation.\r\n<h2>Get in Touch with Us Today</h2>\r\nDon’t freeze your way through a Minneapolis winter with an old or malfunctioning furnace. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers comfort to every degree and specializes in both electric and gas furnace installation. While you’re here at our website, be sure to check out our coupon offers to save yourself even more money. <strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact one of our representatives</a> today at 952-647-0099.</strong>','Furnace Installation','','inherit','open','open','','263-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:48:47','2013-09-19 17:48:47','',263,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/263-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(569,1,'2013-09-20 16:21:55','2013-09-20 16:21:55','<h1>Seasonal Furnace Maintenance</h1>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air has helped Minneapolis stay comfortable during the summer season, and we can do the same for the winter season. Make sure that your furnace is always in tip-top shape with furnace maintenance. We offer electric furnace maintenance as well as gas furnace maintenance to help you get the most out of your unit and to keep you from having to pay for unnecessary major repairs.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-exchangers/\">Heat Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating/\">Zone Heating</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How to Maintain Your Home’s Furnace</h2>\r\nDepending on the type of unit that you have, there are certain tips that you’ll follow for furnace maintenance. For gas furnace maintenance, you’ll want to:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Check for gas leaks</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure that your thermostat is properly working</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure that the control valve is open</li>\r\n	<li>Switch out the air filter</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you’re in need of electric furnace maintenance, you can:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>See if you have any frayed or damaged wires</li>\r\n	<li>Replace burnt out fuses</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure the blower fan is working properly</li>\r\n	<li>Check the heating mechanism’s amps</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe understand how frustrating it can be to have a furnace that isn’t working properly, but sometimes there are easy fixes to your heating problems. Take a look at the manual before you give us a call to see if all you have to do is flip a switch or change a setting to solve your problem.\r\n<h2>Scheduled Furnace Maintenance Saves You Time</h2>\r\nBe proactive when it comes to your furnace maintenance needs. We recommended that you schedule a planned service appointment with us before the winter season blows in to save yourself some time and possibly even some money.\r\n<h2>Contact Us Today</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air helps the Minneapolis area take care of all of their heating, air and furnace maintenance needs. We offer homeowners night and weekend appointments, 24-hour emergency repair services and specialize in both gas furnace maintenance and electric furnace maintenance. All of our work is carried out by certified technicians who have undergone background checks, and we offer free estimates on any new equipment that you might need.\r\n\r\n<strong>To schedule furnace maintenance for your home, get in touch with us by calling 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a>.</strong>','Furnace Maintenance','','inherit','open','open','','261-revision-v1','','','2013-09-20 16:21:55','2013-09-20 16:21:55','',261,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/261-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(499,1,'2013-09-19 17:49:01','2013-09-19 17:49:01','<h1>Seasonal Furnace Maintenance</h1>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air has helped Minneapolis stay comfortable during the summer season, and we can do the same for the winter season. Make sure that your furnace is always in tip-top shape with furnace maintenance. We offer electric furnace maintenance as well as gas furnace maintenance to help you get the most out of your unit and to keep you from having to pay for unnecessary major repairs.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-exchangers/\">Heat Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating/\">Zone Heating</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How to Maintain Your Home’s Furnace</h2>\r\nDepending on the type of unit that you have, there are certain tips that you’ll follow for furnace maintenance. For gas furnace maintenance, you’ll want to:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Check for gas leaks</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure that your thermostat is properly working</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure that the control valve is open</li>\r\n	<li>Switch out the air filter</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you’re in need of electric furnace maintenance, you can:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>See if you have any frayed or damaged wires</li>\r\n	<li>Replace burnt out fuses</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure the blower fan is working properly</li>\r\n	<li>Check the heating mechanism’s amps</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe understand how frustrating it can be to have a furnace that isn’t working properly, but sometimes there are easy fixes to your heating problems. Take a look at the manual before you give us a call to see if all you have to do is flip a switch or change a setting to solve your problem.\r\n<h2>Scheduled Furnace Maintenance Saves You Time</h2>\r\nBe proactive when it comes to your furnace maintenance needs. We recommended that you schedule a <a title=\"Service Plans\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/service-plans/\">planned service</a> appointment with us before the winter season blows in to save yourself some time and possibly even some money.\r\n<h2>Contact Us Today</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air helps the Minneapolis area take care of all of their heating, air and furnace maintenance needs. We offer homeowners night and weekend appointments, 24-hour emergency repair services and specialize in both gas furnace maintenance and electric furnace maintenance. All of our work is carried out by certified technicians who have undergone background checks, and we offer free estimates on any new equipment that you might need.\r\n\r\n<strong>To schedule furnace maintenance for your home, get in touch with us by calling 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a>.</strong>','Furnace Maintenance','','inherit','open','open','','261-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:49:01','2013-09-19 17:49:01','',261,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/261-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(500,1,'2013-09-19 17:49:20','2013-09-19 17:49:20','<h1>Affordable Furnace Repair</h1>\r\nWhen winter comes in Minneapolis, every home needs a furnace that works. If something happens to your furnace system and you need emergency furnace repair, contact the professional at Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air. Our trained technicians have a combined 200 years of experience working with all types of furnaces, and can get you the service you need right away to resolve your heating issues.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-exchangers/\">Heat Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating/\">Zone Heating</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Common Problems with Furnaces</h2>\r\nA furnace is a complex system with a lot of parts that all need to be working in order to provide heat for your home. While there may be hundreds of reasons that your furnace is not working properly, the most common problems that we see are:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Issues with the thermostat that cause the heat or fan to malfunction, or the temperature inside your home to get too hot or too cold.</li>\r\n	<li>Air flow issues caused by worn or broken fan motors, belts, and bearings.</li>\r\n	<li>Filters that are dirty or clogged, restricting air flow and preventing the system from properly heating the air.</li>\r\n	<li>Pilot or ignition problems, which can shut off a heating unit entirely and not allow any warm air through.</li>\r\n	<li>Lack of regular or routine maintenance, resulting in higher energy costs from inefficient operation, and often leading to inconvenient and unexpected system failure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTo prevent problems with your furnace, call our team to provide regular maintenance and check-ups. If you find that you already have a problem, we can help you get the electric, oil, or gas furnace repair done quickly so you don’t have to suffer through the winter months with a broken unit.\r\n<h2>Emergency Furnace Repair You Can Count On</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air we offer emergency furnace repairs by qualified, trained technicians. Every member of our team has passed a background check, and is equipped with the latest tools and technology to fix any type of furnace. We also work to ensure our team is up to date with trends in the heating and cooling industry so they can provide the most efficient and effective repairs, and we offer convenient night and weekend appointments, as well as free estimates on your service.\r\n\r\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact us</a> today at 952-647-0099 to have one of our trusted furnace repair technicians take a look at your system and find out what needs to be done to restore warmth and comfort to your Minneapolis home.</strong>','Furnace Repair','','inherit','open','open','','257-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:49:20','2013-09-19 17:49:20','',257,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/257-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(501,1,'2013-09-19 17:49:31','2013-09-19 17:49:31','<h1>Furnace Replacement for Damaged Units</h1>\r\nA <a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">furnace</a> is a long-term investment designed to last many years, but just like any other appliance, it can wear down over time; when it does, Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air can help you with furnace replacement for your old unit. Maintaining a comfortable and healthy home means having an efficient and effective furnace, and the wrong time to wish you had replaced your furnace is when it fails in the middle of a cold Minneapolis winter night.\r\n\r\nBlue Ox can help assess your current unit to find out if it needs replacement, and identify the furnace replacement cost as well as the timeline to get a new system. If your system is already damaged, we can help you determine whether it would be more beneficial to repair it or go with furnace replacement.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-exchangers/\">Heat Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating/\">Zone Heating</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>When to Repair and When to Replace a Furnace</h2>\r\nSometimes it can be difficult to know whether you should repair your existing furnace or replace it with a new one. Since furnace replacement costs can be high, many homeowners prefer to pay for repairs, but it’s important to know the warning signs that indicate you need a new furnace:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Your furnace is old</strong>. Furnaces that are older than 15-20 years are likely inefficient, and should be replaced before a major problem occurs.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Your monthly utility bills are increasing</strong>. Higher utility bills often indicate an inefficient system that has to run longer to provide the same amount of heat.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>The thermostats are inconsistent</strong>. If you are constantly adjusting the thermostat to try and find the right temperature, the furnace may not be distributing air properly.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>You are spending a lot on repairs</strong>. As a furnace ages, the costs to repair can be expensive, and frequent. Instead of spending more money to repair an inefficient and old furnace, consider getting a new one.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Your furnace is making noises</strong>. While all furnaces make a little bit of noise, excessive noise or strange sounds like banging, popping, and rattling can indicate a problem.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Professional Repairs Offered 24 Hours a Day</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air hires only the highest quality technicians to replace your old furnace. We offer 24-hour repair services for emergency situations and can come to your house any time of the day or night that you experience problems with your furnace. You can rest assured when you hire Blue Ox that our technicians will provide the highest level of customer service and professionalism. Every member of our team has passed a background check and has the proper training and experience to quickly diagnose and resolve issues with all types of furnaces, no matter what time of the day or night.\r\n\r\n<strong>Don’t wait for your old furnace to quit, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us</a> today at 952-647-0099 to get a brand new, energy efficient furnace installed by our team of trained furnace replacement professionals.</strong>','Furnace Replacement','','inherit','open','open','','259-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:49:31','2013-09-19 17:49:31','',259,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/259-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(502,1,'2013-09-19 17:49:46','2013-09-19 17:49:46','<h1>Quality Furnace Service</h1>\r\nA furnace is the last line of defense for your family’s comfort when the temperatures drop in Minneapolis. If you are suffering with an old, inefficient, or broken furnace, we can help. Our experienced technicians provide the highest quality service to repair your existing unit and get it working the way it should, or replace your furnace with a brand new one that provides the right level of warmth for your home.\r\n\r\nThe Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air team has over 200 years of combined experience working with all different types of furnaces, so you get peace of mind knowing that you are getting the best service for all different types of furnaces and heating systems.\r\n<h2>Our Furnace Services</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers a range of services for your furnace, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\"><strong>Furnace repair</strong></a> for all different furnace types, including gas (forced-air furnace), oil, and electric furnaces.</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\"><strong>Furnace replacement</strong></a> for systems that are older and/or cannot be repaired.</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\"><strong>Furnace installation</strong></a> for families looking to build a new home.</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\"><strong>Furnace maintenance</strong></a> for keeping your unit healthy and working all year long.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe start with a full diagnostic analysis of your current system and your home so we can identify the right furnace to fit the space that you have. Even though some people think bigger is always better, when it comes to your heating and cooling system, having a furnace that is too large or too small for your home can waste energy and cost you money.\r\n\r\nOur experienced repair and installation technicians can help you find the system that is right for you, and get it installed quickly and easily. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air technicians have all passed background checks, are trained in the latest industry advancements and trends, and equipped with state-of-the-art tools and technology to diagnose and solve your furnace problems.\r\n<h2>How Furnaces Work</h2>\r\nYour furnace heats your home by taking cool air from outside, heating it, then distributing it through a series of ducts. There are three main types of furnaces available today.\r\n<h3>Natural Gas Furnace</h3>\r\nA natural gas furnace, also called a forced-air furnace, pulls cool air from the rooms then passes it through a heat exchanger where the gas ignites a burner inside a combustion chamber. The warm air is distributed back to the rooms through the same duct system, and vents exhaust outside the home.\r\n<h3>Oil Furnace</h3>\r\nAn oil furnace operates similar to a forced-air furnace, but uses oil that is burned into a fine mist so it can be absorbed into the air and carried to the rooms through ducts.\r\n<h3>Electric Furnace</h3>\r\nThese furnaces use heated coils to warm air that is blown through the system, then distributed to the home through ducts. They are also commonly used with heat pumps and central air conditioners.\r\n<h2>Contact Us Today</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, we have several options for furnaces and furnace service that will fit every home. <strong>Give us a call at <strong>952-647-0099</strong> or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to find out how we can help you with your heating needs.</strong>','Furnaces','','inherit','open','open','','255-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:49:46','2013-09-19 17:49:46','',255,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/255-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(503,1,'2013-09-19 17:50:00','2013-09-19 17:50:00','<h1>Heat Pump Service</h1>\r\nNo matter how hot or how cold it is outside, a heat pump can help make sure that your home’s central heating and cooling system isn’t working too hard. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers heat pump installation as well as heat pump service. It’s a great idea to think about getting a heat pump for your home if you’re looking for ways to cut back on your heating bills in the winter and your cooling bills in the summer.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-exchangers/\">Heat Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating/\">Zone Heating</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Different Types of Heat Pumps</h2>\r\nYou’ll have several options to choose from when you’re ready to start researching heat pumps for your home. Heat pump options include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Gas heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Electric heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Mini-split heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Geothermal heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Air-source heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Cold climate heat pumps</li>\r\n	<li>Ductless heat pumps</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAs you’re reading about the different types of heat pumps and learning more about heat pump installation and heat pump service, remember that each type of heat pump comes with its own limitations, disadvantages, and advantages.\r\n<h2>How Heat Pumps Save You Money</h2>\r\nHeat pumps are always shifting warm air from where it’s not need to where it is needed. During the winter season, heat pumps pull heat from outside your home to the inside of your home, and during the summer they pull heat from inside of your home and shift it outside. This allows your air conditioner to work more efficiently without you having to make any adjustments to it.\r\n\r\nAnother advantage of getting a heat pump is that it only moves heat around rather than actually generating it, which makes it work more efficiently. After your heat pump installation, the unit will run on electricity and save you on fuel consumption.\r\n<h2>Contact Us Today</h2>\r\nIf you already have a pump for your home and are in need of heat pump service, let Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air be the first to know. Before you call to set up a service appointment, make sure you check out our homepage to see if we have any coupons that you can use.\r\n\r\n<strong>Prepare your home for the winter season by calling us at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us Online\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a>.</strong>','Heat Pumps','','inherit','open','open','','267-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:50:00','2013-09-19 17:50:00','',267,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/267-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(504,1,'2013-09-19 17:50:13','2013-09-19 17:50:13','<h1>Home Heat Exchangers</h1>\r\nMake your home heater more efficient with the use of a home heat exchanger. At Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, we realize how expensive it can be to heat up your home and understand that you want to do everything you can to save money while still keeping warm. A heat exchanger helps to spread or exchange heat throughout your home.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating/\">Zone Heating</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Heat Exchangers Work</h2>\r\nIf you’re using an air-to-air recuperative heat exchanger, both the outgoing and the incoming air is divided by a duct wall or another type of solid barrier. If the temperature between the two air flows has enough difference, the heat from the warmer flow of air is transmitted through the duct wall to the cooler flow of air. If you understand the laws of thermodynamics, then you already know that heat will always shift from a hotter space to a colder space.\r\n\r\nIf you’re using the heat exchanger with a furnace, the process goes as follows:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hot gasses flow into the exchanger</li>\r\n	<li>Air flows over the exterior walls of the air-to-heat exchanger</li>\r\n	<li>Cooled gasses are passed outside</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Advantages to Installing a Heat Exchanger</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air recommends that you invest in a quality heat exchanger because they’re adaptable to different environments, compact, more affordable and easier to clean. One of the biggest advantages of using heat exchangers is that they can work efficiently even at the lowest temperature differences. Something else to think about with a home heat exchanger is that it’s easy to install, so you won’t have to worry about calling to schedule an appointment or paying someone to install your exchanger.\r\n<h2>Let Us to Help You Today</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers the Minneapolis area an extensive amount of knowledge and experience, so be sure to let us be the first to know when you’re thinking about getting an air-to-heat exchanger for your home. <strong>Get in touch with us today by calling 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us Online\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a> if you’re ready to experience comfort to every degree.</strong>','Home Heat Exchangers','','inherit','open','open','','265-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:50:13','2013-09-19 17:50:13','',265,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/265-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (505,1,'2013-09-19 17:50:24','2013-09-19 17:50:24','<h1>Zone Heating Systems</h1>\r\nAre you tired of burning up in your own home because your spouse likes the temperature ‘warm and cozy’? Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air has the solution to your <a title=\"Thermostats\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/thermostats/\">thermostat</a> dilemma. Zone heating systems divide your house up into specific areas, allowing you to program the temperature of each zone accordingly.\r\n\r\nOur competent heating professionals are proud to install, repair, and maintain zone heaters for customers in the Minneapolis and Twin Cities areas. Whether your family has trouble agreeing on a comfortable temperature or you have rooms in the home that are unoccupied, zone heating can be a definite benefit to your home.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-exchangers/\">Heat Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Reasons to Switch to Zone Heating</h2>\r\nIf you have considered switching your home heating system and are interested in saving energy, here are a few reasons why this energy system may be for you:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Save Money</strong>: You can save a substantial a