 home’s interior structure. When it comes to energy efficiency, much of where you lose it is as air flows through the air ducts. By offering custom elbows, flex connectors, transitions and plenums, we help to maximize your duct space while also ensuring that air isn’t lost as is travels to vents.</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Insulated Duct Systems\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/ductwork-insulation/\"><strong>Insulated Duct Systems</strong></a>: Most people are mindful of the insulation within their walls, but what about inside their air ducts? Insulated air duct systems help improve your comfort within your home by controlling heat loss or gain, reducing condensation, and controlling the noise that your system makes while in use.</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Thermostats\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/thermostats/\"><strong>Thermostats</strong></a>: Your thermostat is the brain of your HVAC network. It senses the temperature within the system and automatically makes the necessary adjustments in output to control your home’s interior temperature according to your setting. Without it, you’re living in either Antarctica or the Sahara Desert. So naturally, we at Blue Ox specialize in helping you select the right thermostat for your system and in installing it in your home.</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Controls\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/controls/\"><strong>Controls</strong></a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Plumbing\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/plumbing/\"><strong>Plumbing</strong></a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Water Heaters\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/water-heaters/\"><strong>Water Heaters</strong></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Call Us Today!</h2>\r\nMake Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air your one-stop-shop-for all other services associated with HVAC in the Twin Cities area. We ‘re ready and waiting to take ownership of your home’s heating and cooling system performance, and we promise that you won’t be disappointed by going with us.\r\n\r\n<strong>Call us at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to schedule an appointment with one of our service professionals today.</strong>','Other Services','','inherit','open','open','','301-revision-v1','','','2013-09-19 17:50:58','2013-09-19 17:50:58','',301,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/301-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(562,1,'2013-09-20 16:18:13','2013-09-20 16:18:13','<h1>Ductwork Construction Services</h1>\r\nAn HVAC system’s efficiency is largely determined on how it fits within a home. Installing a system that is not fit to the unique aspects of your home can be like trying to hammer a square peg into a round hole, and can ultimately cost you up to 40% of the system’s designed efficiency.\r\n\r\nThe ductwork is the backbone of your home’s HVAC system, delivering air from your air conditioner or furnace. It’s this stage of the home heating and cooling process that most influences your system’s energy efficiency. That’s why Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers services in custom ductwork fitting to ensure that your system matches your structure. We do our own ductwork construction after determining how and where tubing and connections will run within your home’s walls.\r\n<h2>Our Other Services:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Insulated Duct Systems\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/ductwork-insulation/\">Insulated Duct Systems</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Thermostats\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/thermostats/\">Thermostats</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Plumbing\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/plumbing/\">Plumbing</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Water Heaters\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/water-heaters/\">Water Heaters</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Custom Ductwork Saves You Money</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox, we have over 200 years of combined experience in meeting the HVAC needs of the Twin Cities residents. That experience has taught us that a majority of your heating and cooling savings come from not wasting energy by pushing more air through your system to compensate for its design inadequacies.\r\n\r\nThese factors illustrate that point:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Size</strong>: Imagine yourself trying to blow air through a length of PVC pipe. Odds are not much is coming out of the other end. Now imagine doing the same thing with a straw, and you can picture the difference. Ductwork is much the same. Ducts that are too large require more energy to push the air through the system.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Special Connections</strong>: Most energy is lost at junctions in your network of ducts, be it at the plenum, distribution box, or the register. Making sure that these connective ducts fit the contours of the areas they’re placed in helps to cut down on the amount of air lost.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBy allowing us to outfit your home’s HVAC system with custom ductwork, you can avoid the financial pitfalls that can come with choosing a “one-size-fits-all” system not designed to meet your specific heating and cooling needs.\r\n<h2>Trust Us to Help You</h2>\r\nPut our experience in manufacturing custom ductwork to work for you in outfitting your home’s HVAC system. We guarantee that our ductwork construction is second to none, and you’ll feel the results in the new-found comfort you have in your home.\r\n\r\n<strong>Call us at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to schedule an appointment with one of our HVAC technicians today.</strong>','Custom Ductwork','','inherit','open','open','','319-revision-v1','','','2013-09-20 16:18:13','2013-09-20 16:18:13','',319,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/319-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(508,1,'2013-09-19 17:51:15','2013-09-19 17:51:15','<h1>Ductwork Construction Services</h1>\r\nAn HVAC system’s efficiency is largely determined on how it fits within a home. Installing a system that is not fit to the unique aspects of your ho