rnace installation. The higher the furnaces\' efficiency, the lower the monthly cost to operate. Even though you might spend more on a high quality gas furnace installation, you’ll be saving money in the long run.\r\n<h2>How Much Does Furnace Installation Cost?</h2>\r\nThe amount that you’ll have to pay to have your furnace installed will depend on the selected furnace, the amount of labor required for installation, the supplies and materials necessary for installation. Blue Ox offers free estimates on new equipment, so be sure to let us know if you’re interested in new furnace installation.\r\n<h2>Get in Touch with Us Today</h2>\r\nDon’t freeze your way through a Minneapolis winter with an old, unsafe  or malfunctioning furnace. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers comfort to every degree and specializes in  furnace installation. While you’re here at our website, be sure to check out our coupon offers to save yourself even more money. <strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact one of our representatives</a> today by calling 952-641-0099.</strong>','Furnace Installation','','inherit','open','open','','263-revision-v1','','','2013-10-24 18:10:30','2013-10-24 18:10:30','',263,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/263-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(577,1,'2013-09-24 17:29:46','2013-09-24 17:29:46','<h1>Furnace Installation Service</h1>\r\nKeep warm and cozy this winter season by installing a furnace for your Minneapolis home. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air can offer suggestions for furnace installation, getting the right furnace for your home, and determining how much electric or gas furnace installation will cost.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-exchangers/\">Heat Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating/\">Zone Heating</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Which Type of Furnace is Right for You?</h2>\r\nWhen you’re deciding what kind of furnace is right for you and your home, you’ll want to start with the type of fuel you want your unit to run on. Your options include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Natural gas</li>\r\n	<li>Oil</li>\r\n	<li>Electric</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYour decision can be based on your personal preferences or the area in which you live. If your home is located in a more rural area, then an electric furnace might not be a viable option for you. If you have central air, then you’ll probably be better off with a gas or oil furnace or even an electric <a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">heat pump</a>.\r\n\r\nWe also recommended that you pay attention to how efficient the furnace is before you schedule furnace installation. The higher the furnace’s efficiency, the better it works and the less money you have to spend. Even though you might spend more on a high quality gas furnace installation, you’ll be saving money in the long run.\r\n<h2>How Much Does Furnace Installation Cost?</h2>\r\nThe amount that you’ll have to pay to have your furnace installed will depend on the actual cost of the unit, the amount of labor required for installation, the supplies and materials necessary for installation, and the type of equipment that’s used for proper installation. Blue Ox offers free estimates on new equipment, so be sure to let us know if you’re interested in new furnace installation.\r\n<h2>Get in Touch with Us Today</h2>\r\nDon’t freeze your way through a Minneapolis winter with an old or malfunctioning furnace. Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers comfort to every degree and specializes in both electric and gas furnace installation. While you’re here at our website, be sure to check out our coupon offers to save yourself even more money. <strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact one of our representatives</a> today by calling 952-647-0099.</strong>','Furnace Installation','','inherit','open','open','','263-revision-v1','','','2013-09-24 17:29:46','2013-09-24 17:29:46','',263,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/263-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(578,1,'2013-09-24 17:30:17','2013-09-24 17:30:17','<h1>Home Heat Exchangers</h1>\r\nMake your home heater more efficient with the use of a home heat exchanger. At Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, we realize how expensive it can be to heat up your home and understand that you want to do everything you can to save money while still keeping warm. A heat exchanger helps to spread or exchange heat throughout your home.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating/\">Zone Heating</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Heat Exchangers Work</h2>\r\nIf you’re using an air-to-air recuperative heat exchanger, both the outgoing and the incoming air is divided by a duct wall or another type of solid barrier. If the temperature between the two air flows has enough difference, the heat from the warmer flow of air is transmitted through the duct wall to the cooler flow of air. If you understand the laws of thermodynamics, then you already know that heat will always shift from a hotter space to a colder space.\r\n\r\nIf you’re using the heat exchanger with a furnace, the process goes as follows:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hot gasses flow into the exchanger</li>\r\n	<li>Air flows over the exterior walls of the air-to-heat exchanger</li>\r\n	<li>Cooled gasses are passed outside</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Advantages to Installing a Heat Exchanger</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air recommends that you invest in a quality heat exchanger because they’re adaptable to different environments, compact, more affordable and easier to clean. One of the biggest advantages of using heat exchangers is that they can work efficiently even at the lowest temperature differences. Something else to think about with a home heat exchanger is that it’s easy to install, so you won’t have to worry about calling to schedule an appointment or paying someone to install your exchanger.\r\n<h2>Let Us to Help You Today</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers the Minneapolis area an extensive amount of knowledge and experience, so be sure to let us be the first to know when you’re thinking about getting an air-to-heat exchanger for your home. <strong>Get in touch with us today by calling our team at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us Online\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a> if you’re ready to experience comfort to every degree.</strong>','Home Heat Exchangers','','inherit','open','open','','265-revision-v1','','','2013-09-24 17:30:17','2013-09-24 17:30:17','',265,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/265-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(579,1,'2013-09-24 17:31:10','2013-09-24 17:31:10','<h1>Affordable Air Conditioner Repair</h1>\r\nWhen your air conditioner breaks, you know immediately. Often times, it seems as though air conditioners decide to fail on the hottest day of the year. Luckily, Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air is available 24 hours a day, seven days a week for emergency air conditioner repair in the Minneapolis and Twin Cities areas. Our experienced technicians will have your air conditioner working again in no time. We offer affordable professional services for our valued customers. Your satisfaction is guaranteed.\r\n<h2>Our Other Cooling Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioners\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioners/\">Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-installation/\">Air Conditioner Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-maintenance/\">Air Conditioner Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"High Velocity Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/high-velocity-air-conditioners/\">High Velocity Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Ductless Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/ductless/\">Ductless Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/zone-cooling/\">Zone Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Common Air Conditioner Problems</h2>\r\nThe air conditioning process relies heavily on specific conditions to be met in order to operate correctly. There are a number of problems indicating that you may need an air conditioner repair, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Refrigerant Leak</strong>: If you have a leak in your evaporator or condenser coil, the refrigerant charge (amount of refrigerant in the coils) may become too low to keep up with the cooling needs of your home.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Change in Outdoor Airflow</strong>: If the condenser experiences reduced air flow or higher outdoor temperatures, the capacity of the air conditioner may become compromised.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Frozen Evaporator Coil</strong>: When the airflow to the evaporator is restricted, the coil will freeze. In time, a frozen coil will damage the compressor.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Leaking Ducts</strong>: Even if your air conditioning unit is in perfect operating condition, you can still lose up to 40% of your energy if there is a leak in your ductwork. Our team is specially trained to check for duct insulation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMany of these situations can be avoided by calling Blue Ox to schedule routine maintenance for your air conditioner.\r\n<h2>Emergency AC Repair Offered 24/7</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox, we understand that you have no control over when your air conditioning unit decides to fail. That is why we offer our worry-free 24/7 emergency AC repair service. Day or night, our professionals are committed to resolving your cooling issues.\r\n<h2>Financing Available</h2>\r\nWe are pleased to accept all major credit cards, cash and checks for our services. We even offer convenient financing options on approved credit. Give us a call and we can go over all of your payment options.\r\n<h2>Let’s Get Started!</h2>\r\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air</a> today for professional air conditioner repair at 952-647-0099.</strong> We provide innovative solutions to your toughest cooling problems. We’ll get started right away on your AC repair.','Air Conditioner Repair','','inherit','open','open','','274-revision-v1','','','2013-09-24 17:31:10','2013-09-24 17:31:10','',274,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/274-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(580,1,'2013-09-24 17:32:35','2013-09-24 17:32:35','<h1>Water Heater Services</h1>\r\nWhen it comes to your water heater, nobody wants to provide you with “comfort to every degree” more than Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air. While we don’t directly deal with water heater repair or replacement ourselves, we have found the most qualified and certified company in the industry to bring you the services you need. For this reason, we have reached out to our sister company in Minneapolis, <a title=\"Benjamin Franklin Plumbing Minneapolis\" href=\"http://www.benjaminfranklinplumbingmn.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Benjamin Franklin Plumbing</a>, to bring you the best services for water heaters.\r\n<h2>Service from Ben Franklin Plumbing</h2>\r\nBen Franklin offers full <a title=\"Plumbing\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/plumbing/\">plumbing services</a> for the residents of Minneapolis and the surrounding areas. They work with our goal in mind to offer “comfort to every degree” to our customers.\r\n\r\nAt Ben Franklin, they offer the following services for water heaters:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Installation</strong>. Whether your unit is over fifteen years old, leaks, has had a lot of use, makes an unruly noise, or uses way too much energy, it could be possible that you need a new one installed. The plumbers at Ben Franklin will explain to you the options you have, which one will be more efficient for your home, and what savings options you have.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Repair</strong>. The water heater repair services provided by Ben Franklin include repairs for loss of hot water, rusty water, rumbling noises, sulphorous odors, leaking water, and others.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Maintenance</strong>. In order to keep your water heater in good repair at all times, the plumbers at Ben Franklin will provide annual safety inspections, tune-ups, and leak checks. In addition, services and repairs done as a follow up to the inspections receive a 15% discount with a 5% discount on products.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBecause there are different types of water heaters, the professional plumbers at Ben Franklin are experienced and trained to deal with both conventional and tankless heaters.\r\n\r\n<strong>Get started with your water heater repair or replacement today by <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air</a> at 952-647-0099.</strong> Let us hook you up with the best services in the industry for water heater issues.','Water Heaters','','inherit','open','open','','329-revision-v1','','','2013-09-24 17:32:35','2013-09-24 17:32:35','',329,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/329-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(581,1,'2013-09-24 18:07:02','2013-09-24 18:07:02','Today\'s well-insulated homes make it easier and more economical to maintain a comfortable environment indoors, but they also tend to trap pollutants inside. According to the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA, indoor air is typically many times more polluted than the outdoor air in cities like Minneapolis. Included in the mix of pollutants are contaminants like dust mites, animal dander, mold, and pollen that can trigger asthma attacks or exacerbate allergy symptoms. At Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, we offer high-quality filtration products designed to improve your home\'s <a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\" target=\"_blank\">indoor air quality</a>.\r\n<h3>Indoor Air Pollution Health Risks</h3>\r\nFor those that suffer from asthma, allergies, or lung disease, indoor pollutants pose significant health risks. Even those without respiratory conditions, however, can experience symptoms like headaches, nausea, congestion, and fatigue from everyday exposure to contaminants. Long-term exposure increases the risk of developing chronic lung conditions and even lung cancer.\r\n<h3>Whole-Home Air Purifying Solutions</h3>\r\nA whole-house <a title=\"Air Purifier\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\" target=\"_blank\">air purifier</a> works with your existing central heating and cooling system to block contaminants from the air that you breathe. A box-like unit equipped with a high efficiency filtration 