 Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air be the first to know. Before you call to set up a service appointment, make sure you check out our homepage to see if we have any coupons that you can use.\r\n\r\n<strong>Prepare your home for the winter season by calling us at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us Online\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a>.</strong>','Heat Pumps','','inherit','open','open','','267-revision-v1','','','2013-10-10 16:54:54','2013-10-10 16:54:54','',267,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/267-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(771,1,'2013-10-10 17:02:07','2013-10-10 17:02:07','<h1>Home Heat Exchangers</h1>\r\nMake your home heater more efficient with the use of a home heat exchanger. At Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, we realize how expensive it can be to heat up your home and understand that you want to do everything you can to save money while still keeping warm. A heat exchanger helps to spread or exchange heat throughout your home.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating/\">Zone Heating</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Heat Exchangers Work</h2>\r\nIf you’re using an air-to-air recuperative heat exchanger, both the outgoing and the incoming air is divided by a duct wall or another type of solid barrier. If the temperature between the two air flows has enough difference, the heat from the warmer flow of air is transmitted through the duct wall to the cooler flow of air. If you understand the laws of thermodynamics, then you already know that heat will always shift from a hotter space to a colder space. An air-to-air heat exchanger will benefit you.\r\n\r\nIf you’re using the heat exchanger with a furnace, the process goes as follows:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hot gasses flow into the exchanger</li>\r\n	<li>Air flows over the exterior walls of the air-to-heat exchanger</li>\r\n	<li>Cooled gasses are passed outside</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Advantages to Installing a Heat Exchanger</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air recommends that you invest in a quality heat exchanger because they’re adaptable to different environments, compact, more affordable and easier to clean. One of the biggest advantages of using heat exchangers is that they can work efficiently even at the lowest temperature differences. Something else to think about with a home heat exchanger is that it’s easy to install, so you won’t have to worry about calling to schedule an appointment or paying someone to install your exchanger.\r\n<h2>Let Us to Help You Today</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers the Minneapolis area an extensive amount of knowledge and experience, so be sure to let us be the first to know when you’re thinking about getting an air-to-heat exchanger for your home. <strong>Get in touch with us today by calling our team at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us Online\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a> if you’re ready to experience comfort to every degree.</strong>','Home Heat Exchangers','','inherit','open','open','','265-revision-v1','','','2013-10-10 17:02:07','2013-10-10 17:02:07','',265,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/265-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(772,1,'2013-10-10 17:12:58','2013-10-10 17:12:58','','Custom Ductwork','','inherit','open','open','','custom-ductwork','','','2013-10-10 17:12:58','2013-10-10 17:12:58','',319,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Custom-Ductwork.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(773,1,'2013-10-10 17:13:12','2013-10-10 17:13:12','<h1>Ductwork Construction Services</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Custom-Ductwork.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-772\" title=\"Custom Ductwork\" alt=\"Custom Ductwork\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Custom-Ductwork-200x300.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a>An HVAC system’s efficiency is largely determined on how it fits within a home. Installing a system that is not fit to the unique aspects of your home can be like trying to hammer a square peg into a round hole, and can ultimately cost you up to 40% of the system’s designed efficiency.\r\n\r\nThe ductwork is the backbone of your home’s HVAC system, delivering air from your air conditioner or furnace. It’s this stage of the home heating and cooling process that most influences your system’s energy efficiency. That’s why Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers services in custom ductwork fitting to ensure that your system matches your structure. We do our own ductwork construction after determining how and where tubing and connections will run within your home.\r\n<h2>Our Other Services:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Insulated Duct Systems\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/ductwork-insulation/\">Insulated Duct Systems</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Thermostats\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/thermostats/\">Thermostats</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Plumbing\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/plumbing/\">Plumbing</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Water Heaters\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/water-heaters/\">Water Heaters</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Custom Ductwork Saves You Money</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox, we have over 200 years of combined experience in meeting the HVAC needs of the Twin Cities residents. That experience has taught us that a majority of your heating and cooling savings come from not wasting energy by pushing more air through your system to compensate for its design inadequacies.\r\n\r\nThese factors illustrate that point:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Size</strong>: Imagine yourself trying to blow air through a length of PVC pipe. Odds are not much is coming out of the other end. Now imagine doing the same thing with a straw, and you can picture the difference. Ductwork is much the same. Ducts that are too large require more energy to push the air through the system.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Special Connections</strong>: Most energy is lost at junctions in your network of ducts, be it at the plenum, distribution box, or the register. Making sure that these connective ducts fit the contours of the areas they’re placed in helps to cut down on the amount of air lost.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nBy allowing us to outfit your home’s HVAC system with custom ductwork, you can avoid the financial pitfalls that can come with choosing a “one-size-fits-all” system not designed to meet your specific heating and cooling needs.\r\n<h2>Trust Us to Help You</h2>\r\nPut our experience in manufacturing custom ductwork to work for you in outfitting your home’s HVAC system. We guarantee that our ductwork construction is second to none, and you’ll feel the results in the new-found comfort you have in your home.\r\n\r\n<strong>Call us at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to schedule an appointment with one of our HVAC technicians today.</strong>','Custom Ductwork','','inherit','open','open','','319-revision-v1','','','2013-10-10 17:13:12','2013-10-10 17:13:12','',319,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/319-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(776,1,'2013-10-10 17:25:53','2013-10-10 17:25:53','<h1>Ductwork Construction Services</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Custom-Ductwork.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-772\" title=\"Custom Ductwork