,'2013-10-24 19:09:16','2013-10-24 19:09:16','',307,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Blue-Ox-Technician-With-Cables.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(819,1,'2013-10-10 22:40:32','2013-10-10 22:40:32','<h1>Whole House Dehumidifiers</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Dehumidifiers.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-818\" title=\"Dehumidifiers\" alt=\"Dehumidifiers\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Dehumidifiers-271x300.jpg\" width=\"271\" height=\"300\" /></a>Many Minneapolis homeowners use products like <a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">air purifiers</a> and humidifiers, but are still missing out on the benefits of whole home dehumidifiers. A dehumidifier makes hot summer months more tolerable, but more importantly, it can lessen the presence of allergens and prevent damage to your home.\r\n\r\nYou can trust Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air to handle your whole house dehumidifier installation. The prospect of installing and maintaining a whole-home system may seem daunting, but we can take care of the setup, answer your questions, and ensure that your needs are met. The changes you\'ll enjoy afterward will make the process more than worthwhile.\r\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Indoor Air Quality</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Humidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/humidifiers/\">Humidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA Filters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Dehumidifiers Help Seasonal Allergy Relief</h2>\r\nWhen humidity levels in your home are too high, contaminants and allergens can thrive. We can help you to get better humidity control. Using dehumidifiers to dry out the air creates an environment that is less supportive of:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mold</li>\r\n	<li>Mildew</li>\r\n	<li>Bacteria</li>\r\n	<li>Dust mites</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis is one reason that a whole house dehumidifier is a smart investment. A dehumidifier that works on just one or two rooms won\'t be enough to prevent allergens from growing throughout your home. A whole-home system gives you control over humidity levels and air quality throughout your house.\r\n<h2>Tips for Controlling the Humidity in Your Home</h2>\r\nThere are many warning signs that the humidity level in your home is at an unhealthy level. Some common indicators that indoor air is too humid include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mold or rot</li>\r\n	<li>Musty smells</li>\r\n	<li>Wet spots on walls, floors, or ceilings</li>\r\n	<li>Condensation on glass such as windows or doors</li>\r\n	<li>An increase in pests like insects</li>\r\n	<li>Air that feels heavy or muggy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAlthough these conditions are undesirable, it\'s important not to overcompensate when you start using a home dehumidifier. Air that is too dry can cause problems as well, such as irritating your skin, eyes, throat, and lungs. Dry air can also worsen certain allergy symptoms.\r\n\r\nGenerally, a humidity level below 50% is beneficial, but anything below 35% is too dry. An appropriate balance of moisture is essential if you want to see improvements in your health and the condition of your home.\r\n<h2>Get Expert Help Today</h2>\r\nWe\'re here to answer any questions that you have about whole home dehumidifiers or creating a healthy home air environment. <strong>Give us a call at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to get more informa