 your ducted system inefficiently creates hot spots in one area of the house.\r\n<h2>Contact a Skilled Air Conditioning Tech</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air is your trusted source for ductless air conditioner installation and repair services. We fully guarantee our work and ensure complete customer satisfaction with every visit. <strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact us</a> today by calling 952-641-0099</strong>.','Ductless Air Conditioners','','inherit','open','open','','282-revision-v1','','','2013-10-25 16:45:31','2013-10-25 16:45:31','',282,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/282-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(826,1,'2013-10-10 22:45:03','2013-10-10 22:45:03','<h1>Ductless Air Conditioners</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Ductless-Air-Conditoners.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-743\" alt=\"Ductless Air Conditoners\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Ductless-Air-Conditoners-300x199.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air understands that keeping your family cool in Minneapolis, MN, is a top priority. Our service professionals also appreciate the fact that every property has unique needs and sometimes a central air conditioning system is not an option.\r\n\r\nWe install ductless air conditioning systems, also referred to as mini-split systems, in homes that require directed air flow without the addition of ducts.\r\n\r\nA ductless air conditioner is comprised of the outside condenser, the indoor unit (which is mounted on the ceiling or wall, or can remain freestanding), and refrigerant lines that connect the two. It is a compact system that is a great choice for any homeowner.\r\n<h2>Our Other Cooling Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioners\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioners/\">Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-repair/\">Air Conditioner Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-installation/\">Air Conditioner Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-maintenance/\">Air Conditioner Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"High Velocity Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/high-velocity-air-conditioners/\">High Velocity Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Advantages of Ductless Air Conditioners</h2>\r\nIf you live in a home that does not have forced air or use ducts, then a central air conditioning system would probably be prohibitively expensive to install. A ductless air cooling unit offers the following great benefits:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Space Saver</strong> – The compact design of a mini-split system makes them ideal for small spaces like apartments, dorm rooms, attics, master bedrooms or basements.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Conveniently Operated</strong> – Most of the ductless air conditioner units come with a remote control so that complete management of the room’s temperature is always within reach.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Runs Quietly</strong> – A mini-split unit provides comfort with a strong but quiet performance.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Ductless Mini Split Systems Are Energy Efficient</h2>\r\nA ductless air conditioning system uses less power than a conventional HVAC unit, saving you money in energy costs. If you use a mini-split system, even in conjunction with a conventional ducted air conditioner, you can have better control over which rooms to cool. Energy efficiency is further increased if you find that you are constantly cooling a space that gets little to no use. It is also valuable if your ducted system inefficiently creates hot spots in one area of the house.\r\n<h2>Contact a Skilled Air Conditioning Tech</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air is your trusted source for ductless air conditioner installation and repair services. We fully guarantee our work and ensure complete customer satisfaction with every visit. <strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact us</a> today by calling 952-641-0099</strong>.','Ductless Air Conditioners','','inherit','open','open','','282-revision-v1','','','2013-10-10 22:45:03','2013-10-10 22:45:03','',282,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/282-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(827,1,'2013-10-10 22:47:56','2013-10-10 22:47:56','','High Velocity Cooling ','','inherit','open','open','','industrial-fan','','','2013-10-10 22:47:56','2013-10-10 22:47:56','',280,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/High-Velocity-Cooling.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(828,1,'2013-10-10 22:48:22','2013-10-10 22:48:22','<h1>High Velocity Air Conditioners</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/High-Velocity-Cooling.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-827\" title=\"High Velocity Cooling \" alt=\"High Velocity Cooling \" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/High-Velocity-Cooling-300x199.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>The technicians at Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air are experts in the field and understand the intricacies of the weather in Minneapolis, MN, and the Twin Cities area. We keep up to date on the newest systems available and are always prepared to offer property owners the best service possible.\r\n<h2>Our Other Cooling Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioners\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioners/\">Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-repair/\">Air Conditioner Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-installation/\">Air Conditioner Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-maintenance/\">Air Conditioner Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Ductless Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/ductless/\">Ductless Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How High Velocity Air Conditioning Works</h2>\r\nA high velocity air conditioner draws air over cooling coils instead of pushing it like traditional AC units do. Most mini-duct air conditioning units use coils with a large surface area which creates colder air currents, thus reducing the costs of running the system while also increasing efficiency.\r\n\r\nConsider the benefits of using a high velocity unit in your property:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Consistent Airflow</strong> – The circulation system of a high velocity central air conditioning system is designed to create even airflow in every room of the house. They generally come with many vents that are appropriately placed throughout the property to better facilitate those efforts.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Fast &amp; Efficient</strong> – Using half of the airflow of a conventional AC unit, a high velocity air conditioner can quickly cool a room. They also typically eliminate around 30 percent more of the air’s moisture than a standard system can.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Smaller Ducts</strong> – Mini-duct air conditioners don’t require extensive renovation or bulky ducts. This is a benefit for those who have older homes without an existing central HVAC unit, as well as homeowners who cannot afford the high costs of renovating their home to accommodate them.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Making the Switch to High Velocity Air Conditioning is Easy</h2>\r\nSwitching from a conventional HVAC unit to a mini-duct cooling system is easy. The small ducts are only two inches in diameter and can fit easily inside walls and below floors or other tight spaces. Therefore, it is not necessary to build soffits or creative hiding places to conceal metal ductwork, thus maintaining the integrity of your home.\r\n\r\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air</a> today at 952-641-0099 to speak with an air conditioning professional to gain more insight on the benefits of installing a high velocity air conditioner in your home.</strong>','High Velocity Cooling','','inherit','open','open','','280-revision-v1','','','2013-10-10 22:48:22','2013-10-10 22:48:22','',280,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/280-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(829,1,'2013-10-10 22:50:06','2013-10-10 22:50:06','','Zone Air Conditioners ','','inherit','open','open','','conditioner','','','2013-10-10 22:50:06','2013-10-10 22:50:06','',284,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Zone-Air-Conditioners.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(830,1,'2013-10-10 22:50:21','2013-10-10 22:50:21','<h1>Zone Air Conditioners</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Zone-Air-Conditioners.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-829\" title=\"Zone Air Conditioners \" alt=\"Zone Air Conditioners \" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Zone-Air-Conditioners-300x199.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>Many Minneapolis homeowners don\'t realize that they can save money while making their homes more comfortable by installing zone air conditioning. Zone air conditioners control the temperature in every room, so that homeowners don\'t have to over-cool part of the home to make the temperature in another area merely tolerable.\r\n\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air can help you ensure comfort to every degree by installing a zone cooling system. We always aim for 100% customer satisfaction, and we know that you\'ll love the difference in home atmosphere that a zone air conditioner creates.\r\n<h2>Our Other Cooling Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioners\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioners/\">Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-repair/\">Air Conditioner Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-installation/\">Air Conditioner Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-maintenance/\">Air Conditioner Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"High Velocity Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/high-velocity-air-conditioners/\">High Velocity Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Ductless Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/ductless/\">Ductless Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Zone Air Conditioners Work</h2>\r\nZone air conditioners use a <a title=\"Thermostats\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/thermostats/\">thermostat</a> in each room to open or close dampers inside the air conditioning ductwork. These dampers determine the amount of cold air that enters each room. It makes sense to set up separate room thermostats because temperatures can vary between rooms based on many factors, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Exposure to sunlight</li>\r\n	<li>Presence of windows and doors</li>\r\n	<li>Level of the house that the room is located on</li>\r\n	<li>Presence of heating appliances or other heat sources</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nZone air conditioning can help homeowners keep the entire house at a consistent temperature. A Zone Air Conditioning Unit is also the best solution for homeowners who want distinct temperatures in different rooms.\r\n<h2>Zone Cooling Helps You Save on Monthly Bills</h2>\r\nHot and humid summers cause many Minneapolis homeowners to spend more than they like on their electric bills. With a zone cooling system, however, you won\'t have to choose between saving money and being comfortable.\r\n\r\nZone air conditioners allow you to cool the rooms that you use and leave the others as they are, reducing energy use. With a typical air conditioning system, you would have to manually close vents in rooms that don\'t need cooling, which is ineffective and can damage your ducts over time. Zone cooling is a much more reliable, cost-effective approach for homeowners who want to keep bills manageable without suffering through summer.\r\n<h2>Start Saving Today</h2>\r\nOnce you begin using zone air conditioning, the energy savings will start offsetting the purchasing price, so there\'s no reason to put off enjoying a better quality of life at home. <strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact Blue Ox</a> by calling 952-647-0099 to get more information or set up an appointment.</strong>','Zone Cooling','','inherit','open','open','','284-revision-v1','','','2013-10-10 22:50:21','2013-10-10 22:50:21','',284,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/284-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(831,1,'2013-10-10 22:52:47','2013-10-10 22:52:47','','Financing ','','inherit','open','open','','expense-report','','','2013-10-10 22:52:47','2013-10-10 22:52:47','',8,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Financing.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(832,1,'2013-10-10 22:53:07','2013-10-10 22:53:07','<h1>Heating &amp; Cooling Financing Plans</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Financing.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-831\" title=\"Financing \" alt=\"Financing \" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Financing-201x300.jpg\" width=\"201\" height=\"300\" /></a>Not only does Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air have more than 200 years of air conditioning experience, we also offer great financing plans for repair or installation projects. We understand that sometimes repairs to your furnace or air conditioner can come as a shock, and there’s no reason for you to be stuck in the sweltering heat or the bitter cold just because you don’t have the funds to take care of the necessary repair or installation.\r\n<h2>Financing Details</h2>\r\nWe offer all of our Minneapolis customers financing in any dollar amount though several sources. Other details of our financing plans include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>10-year payment terms</li>\r\n	<li>Reduced APR financing</li>\r\n	<li>Options for 0% interest</li>\r\n	<li>Financing for both repairs and installations</li>\r\n	<li>An easy application process</li>\r\n	<li>Instant decisions for a majority of applications</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you suspect that a problem with your air conditioner or furnace might be an expensive one, you’ll be pleased to know that we also offer free equipment replacement estimates so that you’ll have an idea of just how much a replacement will cost.\r\n<h2>Finance with Us Today!</h2>\r\nKeep the temperature comfortable in your home throughout the year with financed installations and repairs from Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air. <strong>If you have any further questions, feel free to <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">reach us online</a> or by calling 952-641-0099.</strong>','Financing','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2013-10-10 22:53:07','2013-10-10 22:53:07','',8,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(833,1,'2013-10-11 13:52:17','2013-10-11 13:52:17','','','','publish','closed','closed','','833','','','2013-10-11 13:56:06','2013-10-11 13:56:06','',0,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/?post_type=nap&#038;p=833',0,'nap','',0),(834,1,'2013-10-11 14:00:26','2013-10-11 14:00:26','','Heat Exchanger','','inherit','open','open','','heat-exchanger','','','2013-10-11 14:00:26','2013-10-11 14:00:26','',265,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Heat-Exchanger.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(835,1,'2013-10-11 14:00:44','2013-10-11 14:00:44','<h1>Home Heat Exchangers</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Heat-Exchanger.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-834\" title=\"Heat Exchanger\" alt=\"Heat Exchanger\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Heat-Exchanger-300x199.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>Make your home heater more efficient with the use of a home heat exchanger. At Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, we realize how expensive it can be to heat up your home and understand that you want to do everything you can to save money while still keeping warm. A heat exchanger helps to spread or exchange heat throughout your home.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Zone Heating\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/zone-heating/\">Zone Heating</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Heat Exchangers Work</h2>\r\nIf you’re using an air-to-air recuperative heat exchanger, both the outgoing and the incoming air is divided by a duct wall or another type of solid barrier. If the temperature between the two air flows has enough difference, the heat from the warmer flow of air is transmitted through the duct wall to the cooler flow of air. If you understand the laws of thermodynamics, then you already know that heat will always shift from a hotter space to a colder space. An air-to-air heat exchanger will benefit you.\r\n\r\nIf you’re using the heat exchanger with a furnace, the process goes as follows:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hot gasses flow into the exchanger</li>\r\n	<li>Air flows over the exterior walls of the air-to-heat exchanger</li>\r\n	<li>Cooled gasses are passed outside</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Advantages to Installing a Heat Exchanger</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air recommends that you invest in a quality heat exchanger because they’re adaptable to different environments, compact, more affordable and easier to clean. One of the biggest advantages of using heat exchangers is that they can work efficiently even at the lowest temperature differences. Something else to think about with a home heat exchanger is that it’s easy to install, so you won’t have to worry about calling to schedule an appointment or paying someone to install your exchanger.\r\n<h2>Let Us to Help You Today</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers the Minneapolis area an extensive amount of knowledge and experience, so be sure to let us be the first to know when you’re thinking about getting an air-to-heat exchanger for your home. <strong>Get in touch with us today by calling our team at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us Online\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a> if you’re ready to experience comfort to every degree.</strong>','Home Heat Exchangers','','inherit','open','open','','265-revision-v1','','','2013-10-11 14:00:44','2013-10-11 14:00:44','',265,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/265-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(836,1,'2013-10-11 14:03:17','2013-10-11 14:03:17','','Zone Systems ','','inherit','open','open','','man-repair-air-conditioner','','','2013-10-11 14:03:17','2013-10-11 14:03:17','',269,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Zone-Heating-and-Cooling-Systems.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(837,1,'2013-10-11 14:03:46','2013-10-11 14:03:46','<h1>Zone Heating &amp; Cooling Systems</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Zone-Heating-and-Cooling-Systems.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-836\" title=\"Zone Systems \" alt=\"Zone Systems \" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Zone-Heating-and-Cooling-Systems-200x300.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" /></a>Are you tired of burning up or freezing in your own home because your spouse likes the temperature warm and cozy or Arctic chilly? Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air has the solution to your <a title=\"Thermostats\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/thermostats/\">thermostat</a> dilemma. Zone heating and cooling systems divide your house up into specific areas, allowing you to program the temperature of each zone accordingly.\r\n\r\nOur competent heating and cooling professionals are proud to install, repair, and maintain zone heaters and zone air conditioners for customers in the Minneapolis and Twin Cities areas. Whether your family has trouble agreeing on a comfortable temperature or you have rooms in the home that are unoccupied, zone systems can be a definite benefit to your home.\r\n<h2>Our Other Heating Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnaces\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnaces/\">Furnaces</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-repair/\">Furnace Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Replacement\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-replacement/\">Furnace Replacement</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-maintenance/\">Furnace Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Furnace Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/furnace-installation/\">Furnace Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Heat Pumps\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/hvac/heat-pumps/\">Heat Pumps</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Reasons to Switch to Zone Heating &amp; Cooling</h2>\r\nIf you have considered switching your home heating or air conditioning system and are interested in saving energy, here are a few reasons why this system may be for you:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Save Money</strong>: You can save a substantial amount of money on your energy expenses every year by simply switching to a zone system. You’ll be amazed at how much energy is wasted on heating and cooling unoccupied rooms in your home.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Personalized Thermostat Settings</strong>: This allows everyone in the home to be comfortable with their own, personal thermostat setting. Now you can be content in your space without affecting the comfort of everyone else.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Quiet Operation</strong>: Enjoy the silent sound of your HVAC system, quietly maintaining a comfortable temperature to your entire home.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Cost of Installing a Zone System</h2>\r\nWith the savings you’ll see on your energy bill, zone systems will virtually pay for themselves. Our zone heating and cooling systems are a great way to manage your energy costs while adding value to your home. Our team at Blue Ox is happy to provide a free evaluation to determine how much a new zone system installation will cost. <a title=\"Financing Plans\" href=\"/financing/\">Financing plans</a> are available as well.\r\n<h2>Call Us Today</h2>\r\nBlue Ox has extensive experience in zone heating and cooling systems and can install yours today. Our professional team of technicians is able to deliver the service you need to reduce your energy usage. We are available 24/7 for all of your heating and air needs.\r\n\r\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact us</a> at 952-647-0099 for more information. Let us provide comfort to every degree of your home.</strong>','Zone Systems','','inherit','open','open','','269-revision-v1','','','2013-10-11 14:03:46','2013-10-11 14:03:46','',269,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/269-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(838,1,'2013-10-11 14:10:31','2013-10-11 14:10:31','','Other Services ','','inherit','open','open','','bright-light-within-air-conditioning-duct','','','2013-10-11 14:10:31','2013-10-11 14:10:31','',301,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Other-Services.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(839,1,'2013-10-11 14:12:58','2013-10-11 14:12:58','<h1>Our Other Services</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Other-Services.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-838\" title=\"Other Services\" alt=\"Other Services \" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Other-Services-300x199.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>Managing repairs to your home’s interior can be a daunting process, especially if there are multiple aspects to consider or different systems that need to be addressed. Coordinating with one contractor can be difficult enough; imagine having to do it with three or four!\r\n\r\nThat’s why, at Blue Ox, we realize that in order to truly provide “Comfort to Every Degree,” we can’t be just a one-trick HVAC pony. We’re proud to offer our customers multiple other services when it comes to fixing or replacing components in your home’s heating and cooling systems.\r\n<h2>Other Services We Offer</h2>\r\nIn order to put the finishing touches on our work with your home’s HVAC system, we at Blue Ox also offer other services in:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Custom Ductwork\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/ductwork-construction/\"><strong>Custom Ductwork Construction</strong></a>: We can fabricate our own ductwork and fittings to accommodate any unique features of your home’s interior structure. When it comes to energy efficiency, much of where you lose it is as air flows through the air ducts. By offering custom elbows, flex connectors, transitions and plenums, we help to maximize your duct space while also ensuring that air isn’t lost as is travels to vents.</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Insulated Duct Systems\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/ductwork-insulation/\"><strong>Insulated Duct Systems</strong></a>: Most people are mindful of the insulation within their walls, but what about their air ducts? Insulated air duct systems help improve your comfort within your home by controlling heat loss or gain, reducing condensation, and controlling the noise that your system makes while in use.</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Thermostats\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/thermostats/\"><strong>Thermostats</strong></a>: Your thermostat is the brain of your HVAC network. It senses the temperature within the system and automatically makes the necessary adjustments in output to control your home’s interior temperature according to your setting. Without it, you’re living in either Antarctica or the Sahara Desert. So naturally, we at Blue Ox specialize in helping you select the right thermostat for your system and in installing it in your home.</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Plumbing\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/plumbing/\"><strong>Plumbing</strong></a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Water Heaters\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/water-heaters/\"><strong>Water Heaters</strong></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Call Us Today!</h2>\r\nMake Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air your one-stop-shop-for all other services associated with HVAC in the Twin Cities area. We ‘re ready and waiting to take ownership of your home’s heating and cooling system performance, and we promise that you won’t be disappointed by going with us.\r\n\r\n<strong>Call us at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to schedule an appointment with one of our service professionals today.</strong>','Other Services','','inherit','open','open','','301-revision-v1','','','2013-10-11 14:12:58','2013-10-11 14:12:58','',301,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/301-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(840,1,'2013-10-11 14:24:46','2013-10-11 14:24:46','','Insulated Duct Systems','','inherit','open','open','','insulated-duct-systems','','','2013-10-11 14:24:46','2013-10-11 14:24:46','',321,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Insulated-Duct-Systems.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(987,1,'2013-10-24 19:25:46','2013-10-24 19:25:46','<h1>Insulated Duct Systems</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignright  wp-image-986\" title=\"Insulated Duct System \" alt=\"Insulated Duct System \" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Insulated-Duct-System-200x300.jpg\" width=\"180\" height=\"270\" />Your <a title=\"Air Conditioners\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioners/\">air conditioner</a> or furnace is remarkably efficient at doing what what it was designed to do: heating or cooling air. The trick is getting that air into the different rooms of your home for you to enjoy. That’s why your ductwork plays such an integral role in your home’s energy efficiency. Some of the energy in the heated or cooled air is bound to be lost in the transference process. The key is to minimize that loss as much as possible.\r\n\r\nAt Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, we specialize in installing and repairing insulated duct systems that help make sure that your ductwork keeps the conditioned air traveling through your home’s HVAC system as warm or as cool as possible. The ductwork insulation is uniquely designed to fit around the duct tubing itself to provide an extra layer in keeping energy from escaping the system.\r\n<h2>Our Other Services:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Custom Ductwork\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/ductwork-construction/\">Custom Ductwork</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Thermostats\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/thermostats/\">Thermostats</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Plumbing\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/plumbing/\">Plumbing</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Water Heaters\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/water-heaters/\">Water Heaters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality \" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Air Quality </a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Insulated Ductwork Protects Your Home</h2>\r\nOn its own, your <a title=\"Custom Ductwork\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/other-services/ductwork-construction/\">duct system</a> is a veritable sieve of warm and cool air. Energy is typically lost through ductwork in three ways:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Heat Conduction</strong>: The US Department of Energy estimates that 10% - 30% of energy used to heat and cool air is lost to conduction through the duct surfaces. Warm air traveling along duct surfaces directly loses heat by contact with the surface. The same process happens with cool air, only with the warmer duct surface heating the cool air.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Radiation</strong>: The energy from heat radiates outward until it reaches a cooler surface, where it is then absorbed by that surface. As that surface then heats, it again radiates the energy outward along a temperature gradient.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Cracks</strong>: After conduction and radiation, cracks along un-insulated ducts are next biggest culprit in energy loss, with an estimated 30% of energy escaping your HVAC system this way.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nInstalling an insulated duct system with Blue Ox is the easiest and most cost-effective way to protect your home from these energy losses. Our technicians know what areas of your system are most at risk for energy loss and thus, where ductwork insulation will be most beneficial.\r\n<h2>Put Our Experts to Work for You</h2>\r\nHelp guarantee your HVAC systems energy efficiency by installing an insulated duct system from Blue Ox. Our team promises to put all of our collective resources to work in ensuring that your ductwork insulation is not only keeping you feeling comfortable in your home, but also allowing you to enjoy the extra savings in your energy costs.\r\n\r\n<strong>Call us at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to speak with one of our service professionals today.</strong>','Insulated Duct Systems','','inherit','open','open','','321-revision-v1','','','2013-10-24 19:25:46','2013-10-24 19:25:46','',321,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/321-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(841,1,'2013-10-11 14:25:00','2013-10-11 14:25:00','<h1>Insulated Duct Systems</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Insulated-Duct-Systems.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-840\" title=\"Insulated Duct Systems\" alt=\"Insulated Duct Systems\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Insulated-Duct-Systems-201x300.jpg\" width=\"201\" height=\"300\" /></a>Your <a title=\"Air Conditioners\" h