 to feel comfortable in your home while preventing health problems. Air that is too dry can cause or exacerbate numerous health conditions, and for many Minneapolis homeowners, stationing a few humidifiers around the house just isn\'t enough to have humidity control.\r\n\r\nHomeowners who are tired of feeling sick or uncomfortable in their own homes should call Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air for a whole home humidifier installation. Whole home humidifiers use your existing duct system to deliver soothing, moist air to every room. This can save you money, discomfort, and even health problems.\r\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Indoor Air Quality</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Dehumidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/dehumidifiers/\">Dehumidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA Filters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Controlling the Humidity in Your Home</h2>\r\nMaintaining a comfortable level of humidity in the home can be a challenge. During winter months, when indoor heating reduces the relative humidity of already dry air, spending time indoors can be particularly unpleasant.\r\n\r\nMany people don\'t realize that dry air can cause a number of problems. Dryness makes people perceive the air as being colder than it is, which can lead to a higher heating bill. Dry air can also cause the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Skin dryness and irritation</li>\r\n	<li>Respiratory health problems</li>\r\n	<li>Nose bleeds</li>\r\n	<li>Static electricity and frequent shocks</li>\r\n	<li>Cracks in drywall</li>\r\n	<li>Gaps in wood walls or flooring</li>\r\n	<li>Mold</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn other words, dry air can be damaging to parts of your home as well as your health. A whole home humidifier can help you protect your floors and walls, increase your comfort, and even reduce allergy symptoms.\r\n<h2>How Humidifiers Help Control Seasonal Allergies</h2>\r\nHumidifiers help people who suffer from allergies or asthma breathe more easily. Dry air can irritate the throat and lungs, and worsen allergy symptoms like sore throat and cough. Humidifiers help relieve these symptoms and lessen the likelihood of a sinus infection developing.\r\n\r\nIt is important to find the right level of humidity, and keep your whole house humidifier clean. Otherwise, you could introduce allergens like bacteria or mold spores into the air. When used properly, however, a whole home humidifier can go a long way toward relieving the suffering of people with allergies.\r\n<h2>Find Out More Today</h2>\r\nAt Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air, our goal is to guarantee your satisfaction and provide you with comfort to every degree. <strong>Give us a call at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to have your whole house humidifier questions answered or to schedule an installation.</strong>','Humidifiers','','inherit','open','open','','305-revision-v1','','','2013-10-24 19:05:05','2013-10-24 19:05:05','',305,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/305-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(975,1,'2013-10-24 19:09:55','2013-10-24 19:09:55','<h1>Whole House Dehumidifiers</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignright  wp-image-974\" title=\"Blue Ox Heating &amp; Cooling \" alt=\"Blue Ox Heating &amp; Cooling \" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Blue-Ox-Technician-With-Cables-200x300.jpg\" width=\"180\" height=\"270\" />Many Minneapolis homeowners use products like <a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">air purifiers</a> and humidifiers, but are still missing out on the benefits of whole home dehumidifiers. A dehumidifier makes hot summer months more tolerable, but more importantly, it can lessen the presence of allergens and prevent damage to your home.\r\n\r\nYou can trust Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air to handle your whole house dehumidifier installation. The prospect of installing and maintaining a whole-home system may seem daunting, but we can take care of the setup, answer your questions, and ensure that your needs are met. The changes you\'ll enjoy afterward will make the process more than worthwhile.\r\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Indoor Air Quality</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Humidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/humidifiers/\">Humidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Exchangers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-exchangers/\">Air Exchangers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA Filters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Dehumidifiers Help Seasonal Allergy Relief</h2>\r\nWhen humidity levels in your home are too high, contaminants and allergens can thrive. We can help you to get better humidity control. Using dehumidifiers to dry out the air creates an environment that is less supportive of:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mold</li>\r\n	<li>Mildew</li>\r\n	<li>Bacteria</li>\r\n	<li>Dust mites</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis is one reason that a whole house dehumidifier is a smart investment. A dehumidifier that works on just one or two rooms won\'t be enough to prevent allergens from growing throughout your home. A whole-home system gives you control over humidity levels and air quality throughout your house.\r\n<h2>Tips for Controlling the Humidity in Your Home</h2>\r\nThere are many warning signs that the humidity level in your home is at an unhealthy level. Some common indicators that indoor air is too humid include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mold or rot</li>\r\n	<li>Musty smells</li>\r\n	<li>Wet spots on walls, floors, or ceilings</li>\r\n	<li>Condensation on glass such as windows or doors</li>\r\n	<li>An increase in pests like insects</li>\r\n	<li>Air that feels heavy or muggy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAlthough these conditions are undesirable, it\'s important not to overcompensate when you start using a home dehumidifier. Air that is too dry can cause problems as well, such as irritating your skin, eyes, throat, and lungs. Dry air can also worsen certain allergy symptoms.\r\n\r\nGenerally, a humidity level below 50% is beneficial, but anything below 35% is too dry. An appropriate balance of moisture is essential if you want to see improvements in your health and the condition of your home.\r\n<h2>Get Expert Help Today</h2>\r\nWe\'re here to answer any questions that you have about whole home dehumidifiers or creating a healthy home air environment. <strong>Give us a call at 952-641-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contact us online</a> to get more information or to order your whole house dehumidifier installation.</strong>','Dehumidifiers','','inherit','open','open','','307-revision-v1','','','2013-10-24 19:09:55','2013-10-24 19:09:55','',307,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/307-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(981,1,'2013-10-24 19:17:03','2013-10-24 19:17:03','<h1>Home Air Exchangers</h1>\r\n<img class=\"alignright  wp-image-979\" title=\"Air Exchanger \" alt=\"Air Exchanger \" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/air-exchanger-300x200.jpg\" width=\"270\" height=\"180\" />With the looming threat of environmental pollution and local codes, many homeowners have installed thermal windows, vapor barriers, and improved weather-stripping hoping to keep the conditioned air inside the home while keeping the contaminated air outdoors. All of these improvements, however, can increase your indoor air pollution by an astronomical amount.\r\n<h2>Benefits of a Home Air Exchanger</h2>\r\nThe blockage of outdoor air exchange can result in stale indoor air becoming saturated with bacteria, chemicals, dust, mold, and other contaminants. The fresh air professionals at Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air recommend installing a quality air exchanger to remedy this problem. Basement air exchangers, and a whole house air exchangers can make a difference.\r\n<h2>What an Air Exchanger Does</h2>\r\nMuch as its name implies, air exchangers are used to exchange the air between an outdoor and indoor space. An air exchanger will replenish your indoor air, laden with toxins and particulates, with natural, fresh air from the outside. Quality exchangers will have an air filter attached to ensure the air coming into your home is protected from allergens, dust or pollutants. The experts at Blue Ox can install a new exchanger into your existing air conditioning or heating system, ensuring your home has appropriate air exchange.\r\n<h2>How Air Exchangers Contribute to Better Health</h2>\r\nThe indoor air circulating within your home can be surprisingly polluted. In fact, it can be so dirty that it can cause or aggravate serious conditions, such as asthma, lung infections and other chronic respiratory diseases. Occupants may also suffer from fatigue, dry eyes, headaches, and nasal congestion all due to contaminants in the air. The American Lung Association recommends ventilating your home year round to prevent your in-home air levels from becoming dangerously polluted. Quality air exchangers from Blue Ox Heating and Air can:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Increase the air flow between your outdoor and indoor space.</li>\r\n	<li>Create a clean air environment by replacing stagnant indoor air with fresh outdoor air.</li>\r\n	<li>Reduce the toxins and pollutants in your home.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">Indoor Air Quality</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Humidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/humidifiers/\">Humidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Dehumidifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/dehumidifiers/\">Dehumidifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Purifiers\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/air-purifiers/\">Air Purifiers</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"HEPA\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/hepa-filters/\">HEPA Filters</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"UV Lights\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/uv-lights/\">UV Lights</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Let us Clean Your Air</h2>\r\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact our experienced team</a> at Blue Ox today at 952-641-0099 for an evaluation of the air in your home.</strong> We are happy to serve our fellow Minneapolis residents, as well as the residents of the Twin Cities area. Our team of professionals works hard to ensure the air you breathe is clean and fresh.','Air Exchangers','','inherit','open','open','','311-revision-v1','','','2013-10-24 19:17:03','2013-10-24 19:17:03','',311,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/311-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(982,1,'2013-10-24 19:18:50','2013-10-24 19:18:50','','HEPA','','inherit','open','open','','hepa-2','','','2013-10-24 19:18:50','2013-10-24 19:18:50','',313,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/HEPA1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(984,1,'2013-10-24 19:20:54','2013-10-24 19:20:54','','Blue Ox Heating & Air ','','inherit','open','open','','blue-ox-heating-air-and-hvac-technician','','','2013-10-24 19:20:54','2013-10-24 19:20:54','',315,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/Blue-Ox-Heating-Air-and-HVAC-Technician.jpg',0,'attachment'