 the outgoing and the incoming air is divided by a duct wall or another type of solid barrier. If the temperature between the two air flows has enough difference, the heat from the warmer flow of air is transmitted through the duct wall to the cooler flow of air. If you understand the laws of thermodynamics, then you already know that heat will always shift from a hotter space to a colder space. An air-to-air heat exchanger will benefit you.\r\n\r\nIf you’re using the heat exchanger with a furnace, the process goes as follows:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hot gasses flow into the exchanger</li>\r\n	<li>Air flows over the exterior walls of the air-to-heat exchanger</li>\r\n	<li>Cooled gasses are passed outside</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>The Advantages to Installing a Heat Exchanger</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air recommends that you invest in a quality heat exchanger because they’re adaptable to different environments, compact, more affordable and easier to clean. One of the biggest advantages of using heat exchangers is that they can work efficiently even at the lowest temperature differences. Something else to think about with a home heat exchanger is that it’s easy to install, so you won’t have to worry about calling to schedule an appointment or paying someone to install your exchanger.\r\n<h2>Let Us to Help You Today</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air offers the Minneapolis area an extensive amount of knowledge and experience, so be sure to let us be the first to know when you’re thinking about getting an air-to-heat exchanger for your home. <strong>Get in touch with us today by calling our team at 952-647-0099 or <a title=\"Contact Us Online\" href=\"/contact-us/\">contacting us online</a> if you’re ready to experience comfort to every degree.</strong>','Home Heat Exchangers','','inherit','open','open','','265-revision-v1','','','2013-10-24 19:48:05','2013-10-24 19:48:05','',265,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/265-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1006,1,'2013-10-24 19:51:27','2013-10