 however, can increase your indoor air pollution by an astronomical amount.\r\n<h2>Benefits of a Home Air Exchanger</h2>\r\nThe blockage of outdoor air exchange can result in stale indoor air becoming saturated with bacteria, chemicals, dust, mold, and other contaminants. The fresh air professionals at Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air recommend installing a quality air exchanger to remedy this problem. Basement air exchangers, and a whole house air exchangers can make a difference.\r\n<h2>What an Air Exchanger Does</h2>\r\nMuch as its name implies, air exchangers are used to exchange the air between an outdoor and indoor space. An air exchanger will replenish your indoor air, laden with toxins and particulates, with natural, fresh air from the outside. Quality exchangers will have an air filter attached to ensure the air coming into your home is protected from allergens, dust or pollutants. The experts at Blue Ox can install a new exchanger into your existing air conditioning or heating system, ensuring your home has appropriate air exchange.\r\n<h2>How Air Exchangers Contribute to Better Health</h2>\r\nThe indoor air circulating within your home can be surprisingly polluted. In fact, it can be so dirty that it can cause or aggravate serious conditions, such as asthma, lung infections and other chronic respiratory diseases. Occupants may also suffer from fatigue, dry eyes, headaches, and nasal congestion all due to contaminants in the air. The American Lung Association recommends ventilating your home year round to prevent your in-home air levels from becoming dangerously polluted. Quality air exchangers from Blue Ox Heating and Air can:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Increase the air flow between your outdoor and indoor space.</li>\r\n	<li>Create a clean air environment by replacing stagnant indoor air with fresh outdoor air.</li>\r\n	<li>Reduce the toxins and pollutants in your home.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Our Other Air Quality Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Quality\" href=