n<h2>Our Other Cooling Services</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioners\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioners/\">Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Repair\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-repair/\">Air Conditioner Repair</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Installation\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-installation/\">Air Conditioner Installation</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Air Conditioner Maintenance\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/air-conditioner-maintenance/\">Air Conditioner Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Ductless Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/ductless/\">Ductless Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How High Velocity Air Conditioning Works</h2>\r\nA high velocity air conditioner draws air over cooling coils instead of pushing it like traditional AC units do. Most mini-duct air conditioning units use coils with a large surface area which creates colder air currents, thus reducing the costs of running the system while also increasing efficiency.\r\n\r\nConsider the benefits of using a high velocity unit in your property:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Consistent Airflow</strong> – The circulation system of a high velocity central air conditioning system is designed to create even airflow in every room of the house. They generally come with many vents that are appropriately placed throughout the property to better facilitate those efforts.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Fast &amp; Efficient</strong> – Using half of the airflow of a conventional AC unit, a high velocity air conditioner can quickly cool a room. They also typically eliminate around 30 percent more of the air’s moisture than a standard system can.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Smaller Ducts</strong> – Mini-duct air conditioners don’t require extensive renovation or bulky ducts. This is a benefit for those who have older homes without an existing central HVAC unit, as well as homeowners who cannot afford the high costs of renovating their home to accommodate them.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Making the Switch to High Velocity Air Conditioning is Easy</h2>\r\nSwitching from a conventional HVAC unit to a mini-duct cooling system is easy. The small ducts are only two inches in diameter and can fit easily inside walls and below floors or other tight spaces. Therefore, it is not necessary to build soffits or creative hiding places to conceal metal ductwork, thus maintaining the integrity of your home.\r\n\r\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air</a> today at 952-641-0099 to speak with an air conditioning professional to gain more insight on the benefits of installing a high velocity air conditioner in your home.</strong>','High Velocity Cooling','','inherit','open','open','','280-revision-v1','','','2013-10-24 21:11:13','2013-10-24 21:11:13','',280,'http://blueox.aigdev.net/280-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1072,1,'2013-10-25 16:40:17','2013-10-25 16:40:17','<h1>About Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air</h1>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-801 alignleft\" title=\"About Us\" alt=\"About Us\" src=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/images/About-Us-300x199.jpg\" width=\"270\" height=\"179\" />Blue Ox Heating &amp; Air is a full-service residential heating and air conditioning company that also specializes in <a title=\"Air Quality\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/indoor-air-quality/\">air quality</a> products and services. We are fully licensed, bonded, and insured to provide our Minneapolis customers with services relating to furnaces, heating, and air conditioning.\r\n\r\nWe are NATE certified and a member of the Minnesota Heating &amp; Cooling Association. Our heating and air conditioning company provides sales, installation, and repair for any number of heating, cooling, and air quality units and parts.\r\n<h2>Why Choose Our HVAC Company?</h2>\r\nBlue Ox Heating &amp; Air was started in July 2013. Alth