er Maintenance</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Ductless Cooling\" href=\"http://blueox.aigdev.net/ac-service/ductless/\">Ductless Air Conditioners</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How High Velocity Air Conditioning Works</h2>\r\nA high velocity air conditioner draws air over cooling coils instead of pushing it like traditional AC units do. Most mini-duct air conditioning units use coils with a large surface area which creates colder air currents, thus reducing the costs of running the system while also increasing efficiency.\r\n\r\nConsider the benefits of using a high velocity unit in your property:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Consistent Airflow</strong> – The circulation system of a high velocity central air conditioning system is designed to create even airflow in every room of the house. They generally come with many vents that are appropriately placed throughout the property to better facilitate those efforts.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Fast &amp; Efficient</strong> – Using half of the airflow of a conventional AC unit, a high velocity air conditioner can quickly cool a room. They also typically eliminate around 30 percent more of the air’s moisture than a standard system can.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Smaller Ducts</strong> – Mini-duct air conditioners don’t require extensive renovation or bulky ducts. This is a benefit for those who have older homes without an existing central HVAC unit, as well as homeowners who cannot afford the high costs of renovating their home to accommodate them.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Making the Switch to High Velocity Air Conditioning is Easy</h2>\r\nSwitching from a conventional HVAC unit to a mini-duct cooling system is easy. The small ducts are only two inches in diameter and can fit easily inside walls and below floors or other tight spaces. Therefore, it is not necessary to build soffits or creative hiding places to conceal metal ductwork, thus maintaining the integrity of your home.\r\n\r\n<strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"/contact-us/\">Contact Blue 